WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.495 align:middle line:90%
[SWOOSH]

00:00:02.495 --> 00:00:04.990 align:middle line:90%


00:00:04.990 --> 00:00:07.984 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:07.984 --> 00:00:19.867 align:middle line:90%


00:00:19.867 --> 00:00:22.200 align:middle line:10%
>> REGINA MEREDITH: This
interview could be called "What

00:00:22.200 --> 00:00:24.670 align:middle line:10%
the Bleep Do We Know
About Suffering Anyway?"

00:00:24.670 --> 00:00:26.730 align:middle line:10%
by film producer William Arntz.

00:00:26.730 --> 00:00:28.920 align:middle line:10%
His new work guides us
through the ins and outs

00:00:28.920 --> 00:00:31.740 align:middle line:10%
of suffering as a DIY
experience rather than

00:00:31.740 --> 00:00:35.430 align:middle line:10%
by interviewing the experts
as he did in his famous film

00:00:35.430 --> 00:00:37.320 align:middle line:10%
"What the Bleep Do We Know?"

00:00:37.320 --> 00:00:39.480 align:middle line:84%
We're now into
metaphysics and quantum

00:00:39.480 --> 00:00:43.082 align:middle line:84%
physics with his new book "How
To Suffer in 10 Easy Steps."

00:00:43.082 --> 00:00:44.790 align:middle line:84%
So first of all, I
think everyone's going

00:00:44.790 --> 00:00:46.200 align:middle line:90%
to want to know, wait a minute.

00:00:46.200 --> 00:00:48.310 align:middle line:84%
We all know you from "What
the Bleep Do We Know?"

00:00:48.310 --> 00:00:49.110 align:middle line:90%
Right?

00:00:49.110 --> 00:00:51.960 align:middle line:84%
And it launched the
careers of so many people.

00:00:51.960 --> 00:00:53.995 align:middle line:84%
And now this is what,
16, 17 years ago?

00:00:53.995 --> 00:00:54.870 align:middle line:90%
>>WILL ARNTZ: Mm-hmm.

00:00:54.870 --> 00:00:57.600 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: I still remember
it playing in college theaters

00:00:57.600 --> 00:00:59.110 align:middle line:90%
across the country.

00:00:59.110 --> 00:01:02.670 align:middle line:84%
And it was really,
in the day, it

00:01:02.670 --> 00:01:07.890 align:middle line:84%
was one of the first profound
films with wide distribution

00:01:07.890 --> 00:01:11.800 align:middle line:84%
that helped us understand that
this matrix of mind, body,

00:01:11.800 --> 00:01:16.110 align:middle line:84%
and expectation and belief
was what creates this reality.

00:01:16.110 --> 00:01:17.580 align:middle line:90%
Now, we think of it--

00:01:17.580 --> 00:01:20.130 align:middle line:84%
everybody kind of folds that
in, everybody watching this.

00:01:20.130 --> 00:01:23.290 align:middle line:84%
But it wasn't known in
that day as it is today.

00:01:23.290 --> 00:01:25.723 align:middle line:84%
So thank you for
bringing that work.

00:01:25.723 --> 00:01:27.390 align:middle line:84%
And then I want to
say, too, that you're

00:01:27.390 --> 00:01:29.670 align:middle line:90%
continuing with this work.

00:01:29.670 --> 00:01:31.807 align:middle line:10%
You were even going
to do a sequel, right?

00:01:31.807 --> 00:01:32.640 align:middle line:10%
>>WILL ARNTZ: Right.

00:01:32.640 --> 00:01:33.150 align:middle line:10%
I was.

00:01:33.150 --> 00:01:35.130 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: You were
going to do a sequel.

00:01:35.130 --> 00:01:37.422 align:middle line:84%
And I want to talk about what
happened, because you did

00:01:37.422 --> 00:01:39.030 align:middle line:90%
a lot of research for years.

00:01:39.030 --> 00:01:40.842 align:middle line:84%
You decided not
to do the sequel.

00:01:40.842 --> 00:01:42.300 align:middle line:10%
You've written this
incredible book

00:01:42.300 --> 00:01:44.700 align:middle line:10%
that we're going to be
talking about today,

00:01:44.700 --> 00:01:47.100 align:middle line:10%
and you've formed a
relationship with Gaia,

00:01:47.100 --> 00:01:49.030 align:middle line:10%
so you're part of
our family now.

00:01:49.030 --> 00:01:49.830 align:middle line:90%
So what happened?

00:01:49.830 --> 00:01:51.720 align:middle line:84%
What happened after
"What the Bleep?"

00:01:51.720 --> 00:01:54.525 align:middle line:84%
What happened to the sequel,
and what's going on with Gaia?

00:01:54.525 --> 00:01:57.180 align:middle line:84%
>>ARNTZ: Well, what happened
with the sequel is I

00:01:57.180 --> 00:01:58.945 align:middle line:84%
started-- it was
originally called "What

00:01:58.945 --> 00:01:59.820 align:middle line:90%
the Bleep, Now What?"

00:01:59.820 --> 00:02:00.660 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Uh-huh.

00:02:00.660 --> 00:02:02.202 align:middle line:84%
>>ARNTZ: And the
idea was "Now What?"

00:02:02.202 --> 00:02:05.310 align:middle line:84%
is like after "What the
Bleep?" now, what's new.

00:02:05.310 --> 00:02:07.200 align:middle line:84%
So I went and interviewed
all these folks.

00:02:07.200 --> 00:02:10.650 align:middle line:84%
And I kept asking him what's
new, what's new, what's new?

00:02:10.650 --> 00:02:13.140 align:middle line:84%
And it turned out there
wasn't that much new.

00:02:13.140 --> 00:02:14.340 align:middle line:90%
I was a little disappointed.

00:02:14.340 --> 00:02:16.350 align:middle line:84%
I figured there was going
to be all this stuff.

00:02:16.350 --> 00:02:21.240 align:middle line:84%
I had one of these guys
who worked on the big thing

00:02:21.240 --> 00:02:22.650 align:middle line:90%
over in Switzerland.

00:02:22.650 --> 00:02:25.070 align:middle line:84%
And I said, what's
new in quantum?

00:02:25.070 --> 00:02:27.660 align:middle line:84%
He said, well, we
found the Higgs.

00:02:27.660 --> 00:02:28.983 align:middle line:90%
But that just--

00:02:28.983 --> 00:02:30.650 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: The Higgs
boson, yeah, right.

00:02:30.650 --> 00:02:32.000 align:middle line:90%
>>ARNTZ: Yeah.

00:02:32.000 --> 00:02:32.800 align:middle line:90%
And that was it.

00:02:32.800 --> 00:02:35.070 align:middle line:84%
And so, you know, I talked
to everyone and I'm like,

00:02:35.070 --> 00:02:39.060 align:middle line:84%
well, there isn't that much
new, and I wasn't that inspired.

00:02:39.060 --> 00:02:41.100 align:middle line:84%
And then I thought,
you know, I'm

00:02:41.100 --> 00:02:43.060 align:middle line:84%
just kind of hitting
the repeat button.

00:02:43.060 --> 00:02:46.330 align:middle line:90%
I'm just trying to do it again.

00:02:46.330 --> 00:02:49.778 align:middle line:84%
And I wasn't that inspired, and
making a film is so much work.

00:02:49.778 --> 00:02:50.820 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Oh, boy, yeah.

00:02:50.820 --> 00:02:51.653 align:middle line:90%
>>ARNTZ: Oh, my god.

00:02:51.653 --> 00:02:54.380 align:middle line:84%
So I'm like, you know,
unless you're obsessed,

00:02:54.380 --> 00:02:56.760 align:middle line:84%
you have to be obsessed
to make a great film.

00:02:56.760 --> 00:02:57.900 align:middle line:90%
And I wasn't obsessed.

00:02:57.900 --> 00:03:02.010 align:middle line:84%
So I just took all those--
all the disk drives

00:03:02.010 --> 00:03:03.523 align:middle line:84%
and put 'em in a
closet somewhere

00:03:03.523 --> 00:03:04.440 align:middle line:90%
where they're sitting.

00:03:04.440 --> 00:03:06.390 align:middle line:90%
They may emerge at some point.

00:03:06.390 --> 00:03:08.880 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Well, you know, I'm
really happy to hear you say

00:03:08.880 --> 00:03:13.350 align:middle line:84%
this because it is so tempting
when someone's had a big hit

00:03:13.350 --> 00:03:17.490 align:middle line:84%
to keep trying to play the
game, and most people do.

00:03:17.490 --> 00:03:20.502 align:middle line:84%
And the information does
become stale and redundant.

00:03:20.502 --> 00:03:22.710 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I've dealt with a
lot of it sitting over here

00:03:22.710 --> 00:03:23.910 align:middle line:90%
in this chair--

00:03:23.910 --> 00:03:25.470 align:middle line:84%
keeping the same
gig going, trying

00:03:25.470 --> 00:03:27.390 align:middle line:90%
to find a little new spin on it.

00:03:27.390 --> 00:03:29.190 align:middle line:84%
And the fact that
you recognized--

00:03:29.190 --> 00:03:32.650 align:middle line:84%
you kind of hit the essential
truths in the first one.

00:03:32.650 --> 00:03:33.450 align:middle line:90%
>>ARNTZ: Right.

00:03:33.450 --> 00:03:36.390 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: And those are truths
that have not gone stale.

00:03:36.390 --> 00:03:38.730 align:middle line:84%
We still have not really
learned to live them even

00:03:38.730 --> 00:03:41.158 align:middle line:90%
to this point, by and large.

00:03:41.158 --> 00:03:43.200 align:middle line:84%
And I'd like you to comment
on that, because it's

00:03:43.200 --> 00:03:48.210 align:middle line:84%
one thing to understand how the
mind/body matrix and the nature

00:03:48.210 --> 00:03:49.050 align:middle line:90%
of reality works.

00:03:49.050 --> 00:03:54.660 align:middle line:84%
It's another thing to have
the discipline, the knowledge,

00:03:54.660 --> 00:03:58.305 align:middle line:84%
the practice to make
it real for you.

00:03:58.305 --> 00:03:59.203 align:middle line:90%
>>ARNTZ: Yeah.

00:03:59.203 --> 00:04:00.120 align:middle line:90%
I mean, it's a whole--

00:04:00.120 --> 00:04:02.340 align:middle line:84%
I mean, you could say, oh,
you create your reality.

00:04:02.340 --> 00:04:05.550 align:middle line:84%
Your reality starts internally,
and you create your reality.

00:04:05.550 --> 00:04:06.510 align:middle line:90%
Well, that's true.

00:04:06.510 --> 00:04:07.800 align:middle line:90%
That is true.

00:04:07.800 --> 00:04:12.210 align:middle line:84%
However, we're also co-creating
it with everyone else

00:04:12.210 --> 00:04:13.360 align:middle line:90%
because we're connected.

00:04:13.360 --> 00:04:17.019 align:middle line:84%
So my reality is not
separate from your reality.

00:04:17.019 --> 00:04:18.089 align:middle line:90%
So that's a big thing.

00:04:18.089 --> 00:04:20.700 align:middle line:84%
And then other things,
even internally, you

00:04:20.700 --> 00:04:22.410 align:middle line:84%
can say, oh, I create
this, but then you

00:04:22.410 --> 00:04:25.140 align:middle line:84%
have all the subconscious
and unconscious things

00:04:25.140 --> 00:04:27.540 align:middle line:84%
that are going to
basically mess it up.

00:04:27.540 --> 00:04:31.050 align:middle line:84%
So you have to do the
internal work also

00:04:31.050 --> 00:04:34.500 align:middle line:84%
to do that and be,
you know, cognizant

00:04:34.500 --> 00:04:36.310 align:middle line:90%
of what's happening out there.

00:04:36.310 --> 00:04:39.090 align:middle line:84%
So it's not the simple
like, oh, I just

00:04:39.090 --> 00:04:41.760 align:middle line:84%
thought I'm going to get a brand
new Mercedes, and it shows up.

00:04:41.760 --> 00:04:43.220 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: It wasn't
the silver bullet.

00:04:43.220 --> 00:04:44.100 align:middle line:90%
>>ARNTZ: Yeah.

00:04:44.100 --> 00:04:46.380 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Now, the interesting
thing about that, OK,

00:04:46.380 --> 00:04:47.890 align:middle line:84%
so "The Secret"
comes along, right?

00:04:47.890 --> 00:04:50.620 align:middle line:84%
So everyone thinks, oh, I'll
just do my vision board.

00:04:50.620 --> 00:04:52.230 align:middle line:84%
Well, and that's
interesting, and I've

00:04:52.230 --> 00:04:54.930 align:middle line:84%
talked about this on a
couple of programs before.

00:04:54.930 --> 00:04:58.800 align:middle line:84%
Because depending on the way
someone constructed that,

00:04:58.800 --> 00:05:00.840 align:middle line:84%
the nature of their
mind and clarity

00:05:00.840 --> 00:05:04.770 align:middle line:84%
and will, attention,
emotion, and desire,

00:05:04.770 --> 00:05:07.740 align:middle line:84%
some people do have that
Mercedes just kind of show

00:05:07.740 --> 00:05:08.820 align:middle line:90%
up, so to speak.

00:05:08.820 --> 00:05:09.840 align:middle line:90%
That's rare.

00:05:09.840 --> 00:05:10.770 align:middle line:90%
It does happen.

00:05:10.770 --> 00:05:14.220 align:middle line:84%
And, of course, they
chose people in that film

00:05:14.220 --> 00:05:17.420 align:middle line:84%
who have a little
easier time with that,

00:05:17.420 --> 00:05:20.190 align:middle line:84%
who it's a more natural
state of affairs for,

00:05:20.190 --> 00:05:22.770 align:middle line:84%
trying to tell the average
person that's grokking it

00:05:22.770 --> 00:05:24.990 align:middle line:84%
for the first time,
you can do this, too.

00:05:24.990 --> 00:05:27.060 align:middle line:90%
No, you can't, necessarily.

00:05:27.060 --> 00:05:30.850 align:middle line:84%
What you mentioned was
really critically important

00:05:30.850 --> 00:05:31.960 align:middle line:90%
a moment ago.

00:05:31.960 --> 00:05:34.900 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, you can set
your intention.

00:05:34.900 --> 00:05:39.050 align:middle line:84%
Then you are dealing with your
kids or your mother, father,

00:05:39.050 --> 00:05:40.540 align:middle line:90%
sister, husband, or whatnot.

00:05:40.540 --> 00:05:42.220 align:middle line:84%
That reality
changes pretty fast.

00:05:42.220 --> 00:05:43.900 align:middle line:84%
Your intention can
change really fast

00:05:43.900 --> 00:05:46.100 align:middle line:84%
if you're, say, pissed off
or something at someone.

00:05:46.100 --> 00:05:47.630 align:middle line:90%
>>ARNTZ: Yep, yep, yep.

00:05:47.630 --> 00:05:48.430 align:middle line:90%
It's so true.

00:05:48.430 --> 00:05:49.830 align:middle line:90%
And also, you have all your--

00:05:49.830 --> 00:05:52.847 align:middle line:84%
in "What the Bleep?" we talked
about emotional addiction and

00:05:52.847 --> 00:05:54.430 align:middle line:84%
how you have those
things, and they'll

00:05:54.430 --> 00:05:56.850 align:middle line:90%
take you off on another path.

00:05:56.850 --> 00:06:00.310 align:middle line:84%
So "The Secret," it was
nice, but, you know,

00:06:00.310 --> 00:06:01.940 align:middle line:90%
there was a whole lot more.

00:06:01.940 --> 00:06:02.740 align:middle line:90%
And I think--

00:06:02.740 --> 00:06:04.840 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: It was too
one-dimensional and not

00:06:04.840 --> 00:06:08.620 align:middle line:84%
instructive enough into
understanding the minefield

00:06:08.620 --> 00:06:11.500 align:middle line:84%
that it is to go through
the mind, the subconscious,

00:06:11.500 --> 00:06:14.080 align:middle line:84%
the emotions, and
that whole matrix.

00:06:14.080 --> 00:06:15.910 align:middle line:84%
You still have to
contend with it.

00:06:15.910 --> 00:06:18.160 align:middle line:84%
>>ARNTZ: You have to go on
the path of self discovery.

00:06:18.160 --> 00:06:18.820 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yeah.

00:06:18.820 --> 00:06:19.620 align:middle line:90%
>>ARNTZ: Bingo

00:06:19.620 --> 00:06:20.960 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Right, bingo.

00:06:20.960 --> 00:06:23.530 align:middle line:90%
So now, tell us what's going on.

00:06:23.530 --> 00:06:25.125 align:middle line:84%
Now, you've partnered
up with Gaia.

00:06:25.125 --> 00:06:25.750 align:middle line:90%
>>ARNTZ: Yeah.

00:06:25.750 --> 00:06:27.417 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: And so
what's going on there?

00:06:27.417 --> 00:06:30.610 align:middle line:84%
This is a brand new
relationship to be revealed,

00:06:30.610 --> 00:06:33.580 align:middle line:84%
to an extent, 'cause I know some
things are kind of under wraps

00:06:33.580 --> 00:06:36.520 align:middle line:84%
for the moment and being talked
about in production circles

00:06:36.520 --> 00:06:38.230 align:middle line:84%
here, but I don't know
what they are yet.

00:06:38.230 --> 00:06:40.250 align:middle line:84%
I don't know if you even
know what they are yet.

00:06:40.250 --> 00:06:42.542 align:middle line:84%
But what are you kind of
thinking in this relationship?

00:06:42.542 --> 00:06:45.400 align:middle line:84%
>>ARNTZ: Recently, I just
started feeling like, you know?

00:06:45.400 --> 00:06:48.080 align:middle line:90%
I'm not doing anything with it.

00:06:48.080 --> 00:06:51.700 align:middle line:84%
And if someone could
take this and develop it

00:06:51.700 --> 00:06:53.420 align:middle line:90%
further and really run with it.

00:06:53.420 --> 00:06:57.610 align:middle line:84%
And one thing that Gaia wants
to do is do a lot of dubs

00:06:57.610 --> 00:07:00.830 align:middle line:84%
in foreign languages and
then get it out to the world.

00:07:00.830 --> 00:07:03.020 align:middle line:90%
And I realized, oh, my god.

00:07:03.020 --> 00:07:05.830 align:middle line:84%
The big reason I made the movie
was to get this information out

00:07:05.830 --> 00:07:10.353 align:middle line:84%
to the world, and here's this
partner who wants to do that.

00:07:10.353 --> 00:07:11.395 align:middle line:90%
So what am I waiting for?

00:07:11.395 --> 00:07:13.960 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: And how's the
distribution, that's for sure?

00:07:13.960 --> 00:07:15.490 align:middle line:90%
Gaia is a large company.

00:07:15.490 --> 00:07:17.800 align:middle line:84%
>>ARNTZ: And then also
the future things.

00:07:17.800 --> 00:07:20.320 align:middle line:84%
And, you know, I still think
well, maybe at some point,

00:07:20.320 --> 00:07:22.990 align:middle line:84%
I'll wake up, and the hand
of the Lord will touch me,

00:07:22.990 --> 00:07:24.070 align:middle line:90%
and I'll be all inspired.

00:07:24.070 --> 00:07:25.390 align:middle line:90%
We'll do "Bleep 2?"

00:07:25.390 --> 00:07:27.490 align:middle line:84%
And even if that happens
now, because, I mean,

00:07:27.490 --> 00:07:28.840 align:middle line:90%
here we are in the big studios.

00:07:28.840 --> 00:07:33.070 align:middle line:84%
Gaia has all the equipment,
the studios to do it.

00:07:33.070 --> 00:07:36.222 align:middle line:84%
And really, half the people
I've interviewed for "Bleep 2"--

00:07:36.222 --> 00:07:37.555 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: --are on Gaia anyway.

00:07:37.555 --> 00:07:39.050 align:middle line:90%
>>ARNTZ: Bingo.

00:07:39.050 --> 00:07:41.470 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Well, you know,
I think it would be--

00:07:41.470 --> 00:07:43.000 align:middle line:90%
this is just my take now--

00:07:43.000 --> 00:07:46.360 align:middle line:84%
I think it would be really
interesting to go in to

00:07:46.360 --> 00:07:47.980 align:middle line:90%
"What the Bleep Do We Know?"

00:07:47.980 --> 00:07:49.330 align:middle line:90%
into that next layer.

00:07:49.330 --> 00:07:50.800 align:middle line:90%
Like, OK, you saw the film.

00:07:50.800 --> 00:07:51.970 align:middle line:90%
You gave it a shot.

00:07:51.970 --> 00:07:54.100 align:middle line:84%
And some of you, you
gave "The Secret" a shot.

00:07:54.100 --> 00:07:55.750 align:middle line:84%
And then you felt
like you were somehow

00:07:55.750 --> 00:07:57.610 align:middle line:84%
a failure at the
other end because you

00:07:57.610 --> 00:08:00.100 align:middle line:84%
couldn't seem to employ it
to get what you wanted out

00:08:00.100 --> 00:08:01.180 align:middle line:90%
of your life.

00:08:01.180 --> 00:08:04.030 align:middle line:84%
And talk about all those
dynamics we just mentioned.

00:08:04.030 --> 00:08:05.320 align:middle line:90%
>>ARNTZ: Mm-hmm.

00:08:05.320 --> 00:08:08.350 align:middle line:84%
Well, one of the things
that "Bleep" also did

00:08:08.350 --> 00:08:10.875 align:middle line:84%
was the idea of science
and spirituality.

00:08:10.875 --> 00:08:11.830 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yeah.

00:08:11.830 --> 00:08:12.820 align:middle line:84%
>>ARNTZ: And part
of the reason I

00:08:12.820 --> 00:08:14.487 align:middle line:84%
used the language of
science, part of it

00:08:14.487 --> 00:08:17.500 align:middle line:84%
'cause I was physicist,
so I tend to go there.

00:08:17.500 --> 00:08:20.200 align:middle line:84%
But back when the film was
made, if you told people

00:08:20.200 --> 00:08:21.820 align:middle line:84%
you were meditating
and what not,

00:08:21.820 --> 00:08:23.620 align:middle line:90%
people thought you were crazy.

00:08:23.620 --> 00:08:26.830 align:middle line:84%
So but if you say it in
the language of science,

00:08:26.830 --> 00:08:29.830 align:middle line:84%
