parking to get their plants

00:13:13.960 --> 00:13:16.090 align:middle line:84%
and their seeds in the
ground and grow gardens.

00:13:16.090 --> 00:13:19.360 align:middle line:84%
I'm already-- I'm one of
them, had the time, right?

00:13:19.360 --> 00:13:22.880 align:middle line:90%
We're already sautéing zucchini.

00:13:22.880 --> 00:13:23.680 align:middle line:90%
You know?

00:13:23.680 --> 00:13:26.140 align:middle line:84%
It's like I've never
had a garden come

00:13:26.140 --> 00:13:27.130 align:middle line:90%
to fruition that early.

00:13:27.130 --> 00:13:29.740 align:middle line:84%
But we jumped on it because
hey, there's some sunshine.

00:13:29.740 --> 00:13:31.060 align:middle line:90%
It's California soil.

00:13:31.060 --> 00:13:33.640 align:middle line:84%
So gardening, people out
walking with their kids,

00:13:33.640 --> 00:13:36.490 align:middle line:84%
bicycling with their kids,
spending a lot more time

00:13:36.490 --> 00:13:37.990 align:middle line:84%
together as family
even if they're

00:13:37.990 --> 00:13:39.520 align:middle line:90%
driving each other nuts.

00:13:39.520 --> 00:13:43.990 align:middle line:84%
They're getting to know one
another in a much deeper way.

00:13:43.990 --> 00:13:46.660 align:middle line:84%
And I have to say this
is odd because it's in--

00:13:46.660 --> 00:13:50.080 align:middle line:84%
we're still in that phase
where people are being,

00:13:50.080 --> 00:13:53.740 align:middle line:84%
thankfully, subsidized with
government checks and such.

00:13:53.740 --> 00:13:55.420 align:middle line:84%
The freak-out
hasn't started yet.

00:13:55.420 --> 00:13:58.460 align:middle line:84%
It's still part of the
calm at this moment.

00:13:58.460 --> 00:14:05.010 align:middle line:84%
And in this space, I've heard
people say that they like it.

00:14:05.010 --> 00:14:07.710 align:middle line:90%
You know, I kind of like this.

00:14:07.710 --> 00:14:09.300 align:middle line:84%
My phone's not
ringing all the time.

00:14:09.300 --> 00:14:12.600 align:middle line:84%
I don't have appointments I have
to be at where they'd always

00:14:12.600 --> 00:14:13.675 align:middle line:90%
overpack their calendars.

00:14:13.675 --> 00:14:14.535 align:middle line:90%
>>ARNTZ: Right.

00:14:14.535 --> 00:14:17.230 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: So there's something
beautiful trying to birth right

00:14:17.230 --> 00:14:18.030 align:middle line:90%
now.

00:14:18.030 --> 00:14:19.140 align:middle line:90%
>>ARNTZ: Right.

00:14:19.140 --> 00:14:20.560 align:middle line:90%
Well, I think I agree with you.

00:14:20.560 --> 00:14:22.860 align:middle line:84%
I think society,
this modern society

00:14:22.860 --> 00:14:26.100 align:middle line:90%
got way off, way off course.

00:14:26.100 --> 00:14:30.090 align:middle line:84%
And the technology that we've
all developed to help us,

00:14:30.090 --> 00:14:34.770 align:middle line:84%
to give us a better life, the
guardians become the guards.

00:14:34.770 --> 00:14:36.660 align:middle line:84%
Suddenly, now, it's
the prison keep.

00:14:36.660 --> 00:14:39.580 align:middle line:84%
And where people-- you know,
I did a software company

00:14:39.580 --> 00:14:40.380 align:middle line:90%
20 years ago.

