00:16:21.020 --> 00:16:23.210 align:middle line:84%
because of theft in
the alcohol aisles.

00:16:23.210 --> 00:16:27.290 align:middle line:84%
Trader Joe's-- within the first
week, I saw people crating out,

00:16:27.290 --> 00:16:33.740 align:middle line:84%
you know, whole cases of wine
when panicking first started.

00:16:33.740 --> 00:16:36.650 align:middle line:90%
So this is one coping mechanism.

00:16:36.650 --> 00:16:39.200 align:middle line:84%
That's going to cause a lot
of backlash and problems.

00:16:39.200 --> 00:16:42.260 align:middle line:84%
Just addictions of every kind,
whether it's food or alcohol

00:16:42.260 --> 00:16:44.450 align:middle line:90%
or drugs, people are in it.

00:16:44.450 --> 00:16:47.240 align:middle line:84%
>>ARNTZ: People are in it, and
it's going to get worse, so.

00:16:47.240 --> 00:16:49.240 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Mm-hmm, and
it is going to get worse.

00:16:49.240 --> 00:16:50.990 align:middle line:84%
So yes, there is
sufficient suffering

00:16:50.990 --> 00:16:53.880 align:middle line:90%
that your book is now timely.

00:16:53.880 --> 00:16:56.600 align:middle line:84%
And so let's talk about
suffering and embracing it,

00:16:56.600 --> 00:16:59.840 align:middle line:84%
because personally, I'm really
big on avoidance of suffering.

00:16:59.840 --> 00:17:01.610 align:middle line:90%
>>ARNTZ: Everyone is.

00:17:01.610 --> 00:17:04.069 align:middle line:84%
It's the one thing--
no one wants to suffer,

00:17:04.069 --> 00:17:05.250 align:middle line:90%
and yet, everyone does.

00:17:05.250 --> 00:17:07.140 align:middle line:90%
That's why there's easy steps.

00:17:07.140 --> 00:17:08.880 align:middle line:10%
Because everyone's doing it.

00:17:08.880 --> 00:17:09.680 align:middle line:10%
It's easy.

00:17:09.680 --> 00:17:11.630 align:middle line:10%
That's kind of the joke.

00:17:11.630 --> 00:17:15.950 align:middle line:10%
And the book started off as
a satire of self-help books.

00:17:15.950 --> 00:17:17.819 align:middle line:10%
Sort of like you
can have it all.

00:17:17.819 --> 00:17:20.420 align:middle line:10%
You can be infinitely wealthy
in these six easy steps.

00:17:20.420 --> 00:17:22.730 align:middle line:84%
You can find your true
love and all that.

00:17:22.730 --> 00:17:25.730 align:middle line:84%
But really, all of those
things underneath the cover

00:17:25.730 --> 00:17:27.790 align:middle line:84%
is an avoidance thing
like you were saying.

00:17:27.790 --> 00:17:30.830 align:middle line:84%
So oh, five easy steps
to be infinitely wealthy

00:17:30.830 --> 00:17:32.830 align:middle line:90%
so you won't suffer lack.

00:17:32.830 --> 00:17:34.040 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Right.

00:17:34.040 --> 00:17:35.490 align:middle line:90%
Suffering is at the base, yeah.

00:17:35.490 --> 00:17:36.907 align:middle line:84%
>>ARNTZ: Suffering's
at the base--

00:17:36.907 --> 00:17:39.710 align:middle line:84%
finding true love so you
won't suffer loneliness.

00:17:39.710 --> 00:17:42.232 align:middle line:84%
So there's all those sort of
subtle connections going on.

00:17:42.232 --> 00:17:43.940 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: So let's
get to the suffering,

00:17:43.940 --> 00:17:46.867 align:middle line:84%
get clear with it first
because there's a lot to it.

00:17:46.867 --> 00:17:48.450 align:middle line:84%
I mean, a lot of
people say, oh, well,

00:17:48.450 --> 00:17:50.090 align:middle line:84%
that's just another
illusion, too.

00:17:50.090 --> 00:17:51.920 align:middle line:84%
When I say I'm not
big on suffering,

00:17:51.920 --> 00:17:55.760 align:middle line:84%
I'm not big on
prolonged suffering.

00:17:55.760 --> 00:17:58.010 align:middle line:84%
On a personal
level, if something

00:17:58.010 --> 00:18:00.770 align:middle line:84%
is bothering me and
going deep, I just

00:18:00.770 --> 00:18:04.580 align:middle line:84%
burst out in tears and sob and
sit with it, and there it is.

00:18:04.580 --> 00:18:06.690 align:middle line:90%
I mean, I can't stop it.

00:18:06.690 --> 00:18:08.840 align:middle line:90%
It's just there.

00:18:08.840 --> 00:18:11.060 align:middle line:84%
And then when it kind
of processes through

00:18:11.060 --> 00:18:14.870 align:middle line:84%
and you think about it and,
where do I fit in this?

00:18:14.870 --> 00:18:16.250 align:middle line:90%
What have I done?

00:18:16.250 --> 00:18:17.450 align:middle line:90%
What can I do?

00:18:17.450 --> 00:18:19.970 align:middle line:84%
It's kind of over then
until the next time.

00:18:19.970 --> 00:18:21.920 align:middle line:90%
But I'm not really big on--

00:18:21.920 --> 00:18:25.200 align:middle line:84%
you know, in the New
Age days in particular,

00:18:25.200 --> 00:18:28.400 align:middle line:84%
oh I'm just processing,
dragging things from day to day

00:18:28.400 --> 00:18:32.090 align:middle line:84%
and prolonging the
constant over-- to me--

00:18:32.090 --> 00:18:36.030 align:middle line:84%
overanalysis of things
that aren't working.

00:18:36.030 --> 00:18:39.350 align:middle line:84%
>>ARNTZ: Well, you know, the
whole New Age spiritual thing,

00:18:39.350 --> 00:18:42.840 align:middle line:84%
I mean, part of that was
like, if you were suffering,

00:18:42.840 --> 00:18:43.640 align:middle line:90%
you failed.

00:18:43.640 --> 00:18:44.490 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Right.

00:18:44.490 --> 00:18:45.390 align:middle line:90%
>>ARNTZ: You're not supposed to.

00:18:45.390 --> 00:18:47.100 align:middle line:84%
So there was a guilt
thing associated with it,

00:18:47.100 --> 00:18:48.050 align:middle line:90%
and that's bogus.

00:18:48.050 --> 00:18:51.240 align:middle line:84%
But what you
describe, what you do,

00:18:51.240 --> 00:18:53.790 align:middle line:84%
that's because you've been
doing self discovery for years.

00:18:53.790 --> 00:18:55.220 align:middle line:90%
And so you realize that--

00:18:55.220 --> 00:18:56.658 align:middle line:84%
and I talk about
this in the book.

00:18:56.658 --> 00:18:57.950 align:middle line:90%
I call it the girl in the room.

00:18:57.950 --> 00:18:59.630 align:middle line:90%
Most people don't deal with it.

00:18:59.630 --> 00:19:02.420 align:middle line:84%
Most people don't deal with
it and look directly at it

00:19:02.420 --> 00:19:04.760 align:middle line:84%
and experience it,
whether it's crying,

00:19:04.760 --> 00:19:08.400 align:middle line:84%
whether it's going, you
know, kicking something

00:19:08.400 --> 00:19:10.250 align:middle line:84%
or whatever you
would do to do that.

00:19:10.250 --> 00:19:12.500 align:middle line:84%
Or the self
reflection, say, I am

00:19:12.500 --> 00:19:16.890 align:middle line:84%
suffering because I did
something really bad.

00:19:16.890 --> 00:19:20.390 align:middle line:84%
OK, what do I do to get-- you
know, and that sort of thing.

00:19:20.390 --> 00:19:22.250 align:middle line:84%
But on the other
hand, like you say,

00:19:22.250 --> 00:19:24.050 align:middle line:90%
you just keep kicking it on.

00:19:24.050 --> 00:19:26.233 align:middle line:90%
Suffering is often a habit.

00:19:26.233 --> 00:19:27.650 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: That's
what I'm saying,

00:19:27.650 --> 00:19:30.680 align:middle line:90%
and that was called processing.

00:19:30.680 --> 00:19:32.360 align:middle line:84%
A lot of people
called it that, and I

00:19:32.360 --> 00:19:33.500 align:middle line:90%
get really bored with that.

00:19:33.500 --> 00:19:34.560 align:middle line:90%
I don't want to hear about it.

00:19:34.560 --> 00:19:35.210 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA MEREDITH: People loop.

00:19:35.210 --> 00:19:36.590 align:middle line:90%
They process.

00:19:36.590 --> 00:19:39.230 align:middle line:84%
And then talk about
emotional addiction,

00:19:39.230 --> 00:19:41.010 align:middle line:84%
they get addicted
to that whole loop.

00:19:41.010 --> 00:19:41.810 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Exactly.

00:19:41.810 --> 00:19:43.190 align:middle line:90%
>>ARNTZ: Boom, boom, boom.

00:19:43.190 --> 00:19:44.610 align:middle line:84%
And when you think
about it again,

00:19:44.610 --> 00:19:48.740 align:middle line:84%
when we were little
kids, we would--

00:19:48.740 --> 00:19:51.230 align:middle line:84%
we suffered a lot because we
didn't get what we wanted.

00:19:51.230 --> 00:19:52.640 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: You cry, and
then you're off playing with

00:19:52.640 --> 00:19:53.210 align:middle line:90%
your friend.

00:19:53.210 --> 00:19:54.050 align:middle line:90%
>>ARNTZ: Right.

00:19:54.050 --> 00:19:56.030 align:middle line:84%
But we have those
neural nets in there.

00:19:56.030 --> 00:19:57.710 align:middle line:84%
And so people, you
fall back into--

00:19:57.710 --> 00:20:00.860 align:middle line:84%
I have a chapter on Buddha
since he's one of the big guys

00:20:00.860 --> 00:20:02.120 align:middle line:90%
to talk about this.

00:20:02.120 --> 00:20:04.370 align:middle line:84%
And I was coming up
with the title for it.

00:20:04.370 --> 00:20:07.680 align:middle line:84%
And the title came out,
Buddha Breaks the Habit.

00:20:07.680 --> 00:20:08.480 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yeah.

00:20:08.480 --> 00:20:11.510 align:middle line:84%
>>ARNTZ: And it is
in not all cases,

00:20:11.510 --> 00:20:15.360 align:middle line:84%
but it is in certain cases, it's
a habit that we just go into.

00:20:15.360 --> 00:20:17.990 align:middle line:84%
And so the idea is
if you can realize,

00:20:17.990 --> 00:20:19.820 align:middle line:84%
this is where the
awareness comes in.

00:20:19.820 --> 00:20:23.180 align:middle line:84%
And if you're not looking
at suffering directly, then

00:20:23.180 --> 00:20:25.490 align:middle line:84%
you just repeat, and
you go on autopilot.

00:20:25.490 --> 00:20:28.730 align:middle line:84%
But if you look at it, and
you go, oh, in this case,

00:20:28.730 --> 00:20:29.870 align:middle line:90%
this is just a habit.

00:20:29.870 --> 00:20:33.350 align:middle line:84%
This is just where I go
to when this happens.

00:20:33.350 --> 00:20:34.570 align:middle line:90%
It's a habit.

00:20:34.570 --> 00:20:37.340 align:middle line:84%
And at that point,
now you have a chance

00:20:37.340 --> 00:20:38.610 align:middle line:90%
to do something about it.

00:20:38.610 --> 00:20:42.810 align:middle line:84%
But otherwise, you're just
autopilot which is so much

00:20:42.810 --> 00:20:43.920 align:middle line:90%
what people experience.

00:20:43.920 --> 00:20:44.940 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Exactly.

00:20:44.940 --> 00:20:47.480 align:middle line:84%
And it also is completely,
and I don't mean this-- again,

00:20:47.480 --> 00:20:49.560 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to remove all
New Age language just

00:20:49.560 --> 00:20:51.330 align:middle line:90%
is a practical discussion.

00:20:51.330 --> 00:20:53.970 align:middle line:84%
But it also takes you
out of the moment.

00:20:53.970 --> 00:20:55.950 align:middle line:84%
When you have this
habit of suffering,

00:20:55.950 --> 00:20:57.700 align:middle line:84%
you're not in the
present moment.

00:20:57.700 --> 00:20:58.695 align:middle line:90%
You're not in now.

00:20:58.695 --> 00:20:59.820 align:middle line:90%
Little kids are in the now.

00:20:59.820 --> 00:21:01.550 align:middle line:90%
They're suffering right now.

00:21:01.550 --> 00:21:02.430 align:middle line:90%
They get over it.

00:21:02.430 --> 00:21:03.270 align:middle line:90%
They move on.

00:21:03.270 --> 00:21:05.190 align:middle line:84%
And then when the
next now comes,

00:21:05.190 --> 00:21:07.380 align:middle line:84%
they go through
their little process.

00:21:07.380 --> 00:21:10.020 align:middle line:84%
But they're not dragging it
forward because children tend

00:21:10.020 --> 00:21:12.060 align:middle line:84%
to live in the moment
where adults don't.

00:21:12.060 --> 00:21:15.220 align:middle line:84%
Most adults have lost the
ability to stay in the moment.

00:21:15.220 --> 00:21:16.020 align:middle line:90%
>>ARNTZ: Right.

00:21:16.020 --> 00:21:17.610 align:middle line:90%
And that goes both ways.

00:21:17.610 --> 00:21:21.810 align:middle line:84%
Either you-- I have
one chapter, it's

00:21:21.810 --> 00:21:24.120 align:middle line:90%
called The Power of Not Now.

00:21:24.120 --> 00:21:27.310 align:middle line:84%
The power of not
now is in suffering.

00:21:27.310 --> 00:21:29.520 align:middle line:84%
So the power of not now, if
you can live in the past,

00:21:29.520 --> 00:21:32.550 align:middle line:84%
and you think about the things
someone did in high school

00:21:32.550 --> 00:21:35.490 align:middle line:84%
where you were embarrassed,
and it screwed you all up.

00:21:35.490 --> 00:21:40.050 align:middle line:84%
Or In the future, you're worried
about something happening.

00:21:40.050 --> 00:21:41.100 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yeah, yeah.

00:21:41.100 --> 00:21:41.900 align:middle line:90%
Exactly.

00:21:41.900 --> 00:21:44.638 align:middle line:84%
>>ARNTZ: So that's the power
of not now is it could really--

00:21:44.638 --> 00:21:45.930 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: --could mess you up.

00:21:45.930 --> 00:21:47.278 align:middle line:90%
>>ARNTZ: --could mess you up.

00:21:47.278 --> 00:21:49.320 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: So and you're
talking about, you know,

00:21:49.320 --> 00:21:51.210 align:middle line:90%
suffering is a choice, right?

00:21:51.210 --> 00:21:54.095 align:middle line:84%
Well, who chooses
to suffer, right?

00:21:54.095 --> 00:21:55.530 align:middle line:90%
>>ARNTZ: Well, we say suf--

00:21:55.530 --> 00:21:57.160 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Well, you say
it's not really a choice.

00:21:57.160 --> 00:21:58.035 align:middle line:90%
>>ARNTZ: It's not a--

00:21:58.035 --> 00:21:59.880 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Like you
say, it's more a habit.

00:21:59.880 --> 00:22:02.560 align:middle line:84%
Because a lot of times, people
say so suffering's a choice.

00:22:02.560 --> 00:22:03.360 align:middle line:90%
You don't have to.

00:22:03.360 --> 00:22:05.485 align:middle line:84%
You can be really smug
about it that way, you know?

00:22:05.485 --> 00:22:07.080 align:middle line:90%
>>ARNTZ: Yeah, people say that.

00:22:07.080 --> 00:22:08.670 align:middle line:90%
It's just a, you know.

00:22:08.670 --> 00:22:13.650 align:middle line:84%
Or people quote the old Buddha
saying, Pain is unavoidable.

00:22:13.650 --> 00:22:15.120 align:middle line:90%
Suffering is optional.

00:22:15.120 --> 00:22:16.007 align:middle line:90%
That's another quote.

00:22:16.007 --> 00:22:17.340 align:middle line:90%
So you're not supposed to do it.

00:22:17.340 --> 00:22:18.465 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: And that's true.

00:22:18.465 --> 00:22:20.360 align:middle line:90%
>>ARNTZ: But, you know, come on.

00:22:20.360 --> 00:22:25.270 align:middle line:84%
A loved one is in a
car accident and dies.

00:22:25.270 --> 00:22:29.308 align:middle line:84%
Oh, you're going to say, oh, I
choose not to suffer over that.

00:22:29.308 --> 00:22:30.350 align:middle line:90%
That's called repression.

00:22:30.350 --> 00:22:30.910 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Right.

00:22:30.910 --> 00:22:32.618 align:middle line:84%
>>ARNTZ: I mean,
there's a certain thing.

00:22:32.618 --> 00:22:36.520 align:middle line:84%
The suffering happens where
it takes you internally.

00:22:36.520 --> 00:22:38.000 align:middle line:90%
And so we sort of--

00:22:38.000 --> 00:22:40.210 align:middle line:84%
if you sort of get
back to the beginning,

00:22:40.210 --> 00:22:43.670 align:middle line:84%
one's attitude about
suffering is so important.

00:22:43.670 --> 00:22:45.610 align:middle line:84%
So if you think,
oh, just, you know,

00:22:45.610 --> 00:22:48.100 align:middle line:84%
lousy stuff happens to
me, that's one thing.

00:22:48.100 --> 00:22:50.170 align:middle line:84%
Or we think, oh, I
create all my suffering.

00:22:50.170 --> 00:22:52.120 align:middle line:90%
Sometimes, you don't create it.

00:22:52.120 --> 00:22:53.500 align:middle line:90%
Just like this COVID thing.

00:22:53.500 --> 00:22:54.090 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: It's life.

00:22:54.090 --> 00:22:54.890 align:middle line:90%
There are cycles.

00:22:54.890 --> 00:22:56.230 align:middle line:90%
>>ARNTZ: It just happens to you.

00:22:56.230 --> 00:22:58.840 align:middle line:84%
So then the question is, how
are you going to relate to it?

00:22:58.840 --> 00:23:01.630 align:middle line:84%
If you're going to go
into the victim thing

00:23:01.630 --> 00:23:03.922 align:middle line:84%
and just blame other
people and do that,

00:23:03.922 --> 00:23:05.380 align:middle line:84%
you're not going
to get the lesson.

00:23:05.380 --> 00:23:09.010 align:middle line:84%
Fundamentally, my sense
is all the suffering

00:23:09.010 --> 00:23:12.200 align:middle line:84%
has a lesson for us,
and it's often painful.

00:23:12.200 --> 00:23:14.770 align:middle line:84%
But for myself, when
I've changed the most,

00:23:14.770 --> 00:23:17.600 align:middle line:84%
transformed the most, it's
due to some pretty intense

00:23:17.600 --> 00:23:18.400 align:middle line:90%
suffering.

00:23:18.400 --> 00:23:20.740 align:middle line:84%
And humanity is
kind of that way.

00:23:20.740 --> 00:23:21.790 align:middle line:90%
Why we're that way?

00:23:21.790 --> 00:23:23.620 align:middle line:84%
Well, we could talk
for many hours on that,

00:23:23.620 --> 00:23:25.150 align:middle line:90%
but that's where we're at.

00:23:25.150 --> 00:23:26.430 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Now, all right.

00:23:26.430 --> 00:23:29.320 align:middle line:84%
Let's say that
suffering is something

00:23:29.320 --> 00:23:31.240 align:middle line:84%
that we need to do
more gracefully.

00:23:31.240 --> 00:23:34.300 align:middle line:84%
We need to do it in a
way that is, let's even

00:23:34.300 --> 00:23:37.210 align:middle line:84%
say, works toward our
growth but is also

00:23:37.210 --> 00:23:40.210 align:middle line:84%
maybe more efficient than
making a habit of it, right?

00:23:40.210 --> 00:23:41.080 align:middle line:90%
>>ARNTZ: Right.

00:23:41.080 --> 00:23:45.520 align:middle line:84%
And when you say
more gracefully,

00:23:45.520 --> 00:23:47.290 align:middle line:84%
if you step back
from that, you say

00:23:47.290 --> 00:23:50.620 align:middle line:84%
there's different strategies
you can take to deal with it.

00:23:50.620 --> 00:23:53.200 align:middle line:90%
And gracefulness is one thing.

00:23:53.200 --> 00:23:56.980 align:middle line:90%
One is stoicism.

00:23:56.980 --> 00:24:00.130 align:middle line:90%
One is surrender.

00:24:00.130 --> 00:24:03.020 align:middle line:84%
You know, there's different
ways that you can actually

00:24:03.020 --> 00:24:03.820 align:middle line:90%
relate to it.

00:24:03.820 --> 00:24:06.640 align:middle line:84%
And again, this is part of what
I talked about in the book.

00:24:06.640 --> 00:24:09.760 align:middle line:84%
It's like you get to choose how
you're going to relate to it.

00:24:09.760 --> 00:24:11.080 align:middle line:90%
That's the choice you have.

00:24:11.080 --> 00:24:13.688 align:middle line:84%
You may not choose whether
the event comes to you or not.

00:24:13.688 --> 00:24:15.105 align:middle line:84%
You get to choose
how you respond.

00:24:15.105 --> 00:24:17.200 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: How do you
respond to suffering?

00:24:17.200 --> 00:24:19.720 align:middle line:84%
>>ARNTZ: Well, it
depends on what it is.

00:24:19.720 --> 00:24:20.710 align:middle line:90%
I mean, you know--

00:24:20.710 --> 00:24:22.210 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: --which
area of life or--

00:24:22.210 --> 00:24:23.520 align:middle line:84%
>>ARNTZ: If I was
doing a self-help book,

00:24:23.520 --> 00:24:25.537 align:middle line:84%
I would have formulas
for all this, right?

00:24:25.537 --> 00:24:27.370 align:middle line:84%
Well, when you suffer,
you blah, blah, blah.

00:24:27.370 --> 00:24:29.840 align:middle line:84%
But it's different
for every individual,

00:24:29.840 --> 00:24:34.420 align:middle line:84%
and it's different for
the what's happening.

00:24:34.420 --> 00:24:38.950 align:middle line:84%
Like, you know, if I do
something that hurts someone,

00:24:38.950 --> 00:24:42.140 align:middle line:90%
my response is to make amends.

00:24:42.140 --> 00:24:42.940 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Right.

00:24:42.940 --> 00:24:45.110 align:middle line:84%
>>ARNTZ: You know, it's
something very active.

00:24:45.110 --> 00:24:46.750 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: You approach it
very actively and directly.

00:24:46.750 --> 00:24:47.830 align:middle line:90%
>>ARNTZ: You do that.

00:24:47.830 --> 00:24:49.460 align:middle line:90%
And you make amends.

00:24:49.460 --> 00:24:52.480 align:middle line:84%
You do whatever you can
to set things right.

00:24:52.480 --> 00:24:53.740 align:middle line:90%
Of course, you apologize.

00:24:53.740 --> 00:24:55.600 align:middle line:84%
But then you don't
just apologize,

00:24:55.600 --> 00:24:57.640 align:middle line:84%
you do something
even beyond that.

00:24:57.640 --> 00:24:59.050 align:middle line:90%
So that's one thing.

00:24:59.050 --> 00:25:00.880 align:middle line:84%
But there's other
times when you're

00:25:00.880 --> 00:25:05.950 align:middle line:84%
suffering of, let's say, a great
injustice, a great injustice.

00:25:05.950 --> 00:25:08.830 align:middle line:84%
You and your friends are
suffering a great injustice.

00:25:08.830 --> 00:25:10.900 align:middle line:84%
So what you're going
to do is you're

00:25:10.900 --> 00:25:13.700 align:middle line:84%
going to start maybe walking
up and down the street

00:25:13.700 --> 00:25:14.500 align:middle line:90%
with a sign.

00:25:14.500 --> 00:25:16.240 align:middle line:84%
I mean, who knows what
you're going to do,

00:25:16.240 --> 00:25:17.657 align:middle line:84%
but you'll do
something like that.

00:25:17.657 --> 00:25:21.730 align:middle line:84%
So really, it depends
on what it is.

00:25:21.730 --> 00:25:25.120 align:middle line:84%
But, again, stepping back
a thing, you look at it.

00:25:25.120 --> 00:25:28.240 align:middle line:84%
You say, what's my
strategy going to be?

00:25:28.240 --> 00:25:30.280 align:middle line:90%
How am I going to react?

00:25:30.280 --> 00:25:33.610 align:middle line:84%
Maybe this is a time, like
you said, to just be graceful

00:25:33.610 --> 00:25:35.590 align:middle line:90%
about it, just to be graceful.

00:25:35.590 --> 00:25:36.565 align:middle line:90%
Just say--

00:25:36.565 --> 00:25:38.170 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: It's here.

00:25:38.170 --> 00:25:40.450 align:middle line:84%
You know, how much
reflection can I do?

00:25:40.450 --> 00:25:42.868 align:middle line:84%
How much can I have
an effect to change?

00:25:42.868 --> 00:25:44.410 align:middle line:84%
You mentioned
something a moment ago.

00:25:44.410 --> 00:25:47.610 align:middle line:84%
If you've hurt
someone, for example,

00:25:47.610 --> 00:25:52.000 align:middle line:84%
a lot of times, what people
do is let a little time pass,

00:25:52.000 --> 00:25:54.250 align:middle line:84%
hope no one really
actually noticed--

00:25:54.250 --> 00:25:55.240 align:middle line:90%
you know what I mean--

00:25:55.240 --> 00:25:57.130 align:middle line:90%
and try to gloss it over.

00:25:57.130 --> 00:26:00.430 align:middle line:84%
And let's talk
about what happens

00:26:00.430 --> 00:26:03.220 align:middle line:90%
when we try to gloss it over.

00:26:03.220 --> 00:26:06.400 align:middle line:84%
>>ARNTZ: Well, when you
try to gloss it over,

00:26:06.400 --> 00:26:08.830 align:middle line:84%
then it goes into
the unconscious.

00:26:08.830 --> 00:26:11.420 align:middle line:84%
And then, you know, it's
down there wreaking havoc.

00:26:11.420 --> 00:26:12.920 align:middle line:84%
And who knows what
is going to do.

00:26:12.920 --> 00:26:16.600 align:middle line:84%
And then you're something that
you're avoiding, so you just--

00:26:16.600 --> 00:26:17.530 align:middle line:90%
you can't go there.

00:26:17.530 --> 00:26:21.400 align:middle line:84%
There's a concept I
talk about in the book.

00:26:21.400 --> 00:26:25.990 align:middle line:84%
It's a concept from the Kabbalah
and the Jewish tradition

00:26:25.990 --> 00:26:28.180 align:middle line:90%
of tikkun olam.

00:26:28.180 --> 00:26:31.580 align:middle line:84%
And the idea is, OK, if you
harm someone, of course,

00:26:31.580 --> 00:26:34.210 align:middle line:84%
you apologize, but
you must make repair.

00:26:34.210 --> 00:26:38.070 align:middle line:84%
That you don't actually get
out of it until you make repair

00:26:38.070 --> 00:26:39.730 align:middle line:90%
and you do whatever you can.

00:26:39.730 --> 00:26:42.070 align:middle line:84%
And it's also interesting--
that's part of the 12-step

00:26:42.070 --> 00:26:42.970 align:middle line:90%
program--

00:26:42.970 --> 00:26:46.930 align:middle line:84%
is that if you do that, you
have to go find everyone

00:26:46.930 --> 00:26:50.710 align:middle line:84%
that your addiction has
hurt and attempt repair.

00:26:50.710 --> 00:26:54.130 align:middle line:84%
And there's something
energetically about that.

00:26:54.130 --> 00:26:58.490 align:middle line:90%
By doing the repair you--

00:26:58.490 --> 00:27:01.840 align:middle line:84%
as my wife Deirdre says-- when
you do that, you're actually

00:27:01.840 --> 00:27:03.280 align:middle line:90%
repairing God.

00:27:03.280 --> 00:27:05.080 align:middle line:90%
You're repairing the universe.

00:27:05.080 --> 00:27:08.200 align:middle line:84%
By doing that repair, not
only are you repairing that,

00:27:08.200 --> 00:27:11.440 align:middle line:84%
but it's something that's
even broader, because we all

00:27:11.440 --> 00:27:12.320 align:middle line:90%
make mistakes.

00:27:12.320 --> 00:27:13.930 align:middle line:90%
We all hurt people.

00:27:13.930 --> 00:27:15.340 align:middle line:90%
We all screw up.

00:27:15.340 --> 00:27:18.310 align:middle line:84%
But by doing that, you're
acknowledging that and saying,

00:27:18.310 --> 00:27:19.810 align:middle line:90%
but there's a way forward.

00:27:19.810 --> 00:27:22.250 align:middle line:90%
So it takes it--

00:27:22.250 --> 00:27:24.520 align:middle line:84%
I mean, so when you have
a lemon, make lemonade.

00:27:24.520 --> 00:27:26.350 align:middle line:84%
So even though you did
screw something up,

00:27:26.350 --> 00:27:28.660 align:middle line:84%
by doing the repair,
you're actually

00:27:28.660 --> 00:27:31.810 align:middle line:84%
doing something overall
that's positive.

00:27:31.810 --> 00:27:33.250 align:middle line:84%
And so there, you
get to the thing

00:27:33.250 --> 00:27:36.160 align:middle line:84%
that the suffering can
trigger something that's

00:27:36.160 --> 00:27:37.930 align:middle line:90%
really transformative and good.

00:27:37.930 --> 00:27:39.357 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: I totally agree.

00:27:39.357 --> 00:27:41.440 align:middle line:84%
And that's when people
feel their most vulnerable.

00:27:41.440 --> 00:27:42.700 align:middle line:90%
They know they've screwed up.

00:27:42.700 --> 00:27:44.410 align:middle line:84%
They're hoping not
to get really busted

00:27:44.410 --> 00:27:46.840 align:middle line:90%
on it because they feel bad.

00:27:46.840 --> 00:27:49.180 align:middle line:84%
But, in fact, I have
always found people

00:27:49.180 --> 00:27:52.420 align:middle line:84%
to be at their most beautiful
and most lovable when

00:27:52.420 --> 00:27:54.370 align:middle line:84%
those vulnerabilities
come to the surface.

00:27:54.370 --> 00:27:56.350 align:middle line:84%
And you say, god, I
can't believe I did that.

00:27:56.350 --> 00:27:56.980 align:middle line:90%
>>ARNTZ: Right.

00:27:56.980 --> 00:27:58.000 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: I'm sorry, you know.

00:27:58.000 --> 00:27:59.333 align:middle line:90%
>>ARNTZ: Well, think about that.

00:27:59.333 --> 00:28:01.330 align:middle line:84%
The guilt is generally
a shock to the ego.

00:28:01.330 --> 00:28:02.680 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: It's ego, yeah.

00:28:02.680 --> 00:28:05.110 align:middle line:84%
>>ARNTZ: So the
ego takes a, boom,

00:28:05.110 --> 00:28:08.560 align:middle line:84%
and then it drops, and then
you get the vulnerability.

00:28:08.560 --> 00:28:13.780 align:middle line:84%
So again, this is where you get
a thing when you're suffering

00:28:13.780 --> 00:28:15.970 align:middle line:90%
that it is an opportunity.

00:28:15.970 --> 00:28:16.840 align:middle line:90%
A doorway opens.

00:28:16.840 --> 00:28:18.098 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Absolutely.

00:28:18.098 --> 00:28:20.140 align:middle line:84%
And one of the things you
wrote about in the book

00:28:20.140 --> 00:28:22.888 align:middle line:84%
is, you know, everybody
likes to believe

00:28:22.888 --> 00:28:24.430 align:middle line:84%
that if they could
just kind of order

00:28:24.430 --> 00:28:27.430 align:middle line:84%
their life around their
wishes and their dreams,

00:28:27.430 --> 00:28:30.670 align:middle line:84%
everything would be perfect
if at all just supported them

00:28:30.670 --> 00:28:32.950 align:middle line:84%
and life just
supported their dreams.

00:28:32.950 --> 00:28:35.980 align:middle line:84%
You're saying that is not
true, so let's talk about that.

00:28:35.980 --> 00:28:37.273 align:middle line:90%
>>ARNTZ: Yeah, I mean it's--

00:28:37.273 --> 00:28:39.940 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: 'Cause this goes into
conflict a little bit with just

00:28:39.940 --> 00:28:41.590 align:middle line:90%
believe it, and it will happen.

00:28:41.590 --> 00:28:43.780 align:middle line:84%
And just because you
wish it and dream

00:28:43.780 --> 00:28:47.530 align:middle line:84%
it does not mean that that
is going to be your life

00:28:47.530 --> 00:28:49.720 align:middle line:84%
and it's even the best
path for your life.

00:28:49.720 --> 00:28:52.420 align:middle line:84%
>>ARNTZ: The thing is, even
if you did get everything you

00:28:52.420 --> 00:28:56.740 align:middle line:84%
wanted just like that, your
suffering would not end.

00:28:56.740 --> 00:28:59.890 align:middle line:10%
'Cause you look at all the
people who have it all--

00:28:59.890 --> 00:29:02.960 align:middle line:10%
lots of money, fame, the whole
bit-- and they commit suicide.

00:29:02.960 --> 00:29:07.060 align:middle line:10%
Or for myself, you know, I
thought I had a couple dreams.

00:29:07.060 --> 00:29:08.552 align:middle line:90%
One was to make a lot of money.

00:29:08.552 --> 00:29:10.260 align:middle line:84%
Well, I did that with
software companies.

00:29:10.260 --> 00:29:13.690 align:middle line:84%
And really to make a film,
a spiritual thing that would

00:29:13.690 --> 00:29:16.160 align:middle line:90%
transform, and I did that.

00:29:16.160 --> 00:29:18.370 align:middle line:84%
And so those were really
my two big things.

00:29:18.370 --> 00:29:21.780 align:middle line:84%
And so I figured, OK,
now I'm, you know, no.

00:29:21.780 --> 00:29:22.780 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: I've done it.

00:29:22.780 --> 00:29:26.410 align:middle line:84%
>>ARNTZ: Well, then someone
cuts you off on the freeway.

00:29:26.410 --> 00:29:28.660 align:middle line:84%
You know, you see
something in the news.

00:29:28.660 --> 00:29:29.740 align:middle line:90%
Something bad happens.

00:29:29.740 --> 00:29:31.780 align:middle line:90%
I mean, then it doesn't end.

00:29:31.780 --> 00:29:36.370 align:middle line:84%
So the idea that by
getting everything I want,

00:29:36.370 --> 00:29:39.550 align:middle line:84%
my life will be perfect
is just an illusion.

00:29:39.550 --> 00:29:46.240 align:middle line:84%
And that illusion drives
people to work like crazy to,

00:29:46.240 --> 00:29:48.460 align:middle line:84%
you know, all the stuff
that people do in order

00:29:48.460 --> 00:29:55.490 align:middle line:84%
to get everything thinking that
that's going to be nirvana.

00:29:55.490 --> 00:29:56.392 align:middle line:90%
And it ain't.

00:29:56.392 --> 00:29:57.600 align:middle line:90%
That's not how you get there.

00:29:57.600 --> 00:30:02.120 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Because our being
is actually seeking growth.

00:30:02.120 --> 00:30:03.630 align:middle line:90%
>>ARNTZ: Our being is growth.

00:30:03.630 --> 00:30:05.940 align:middle line:84%
And it's really--
and all the stuff

00:30:05.940 --> 00:30:08.220 align:middle line:84%
that you want, again,
that's external.

00:30:08.220 --> 00:30:10.200 align:middle line:90%
That's in the world of the ego.

00:30:10.200 --> 00:30:16.580 align:middle line:84%
But really, the joy that you
get is on the soul level.

00:30:16.580 --> 00:30:19.440 align:middle line:90%
It's that inner part of you.

00:30:19.440 --> 00:30:23.040 align:middle line:84%
And I've been thinking
a lot about what--

00:30:23.040 --> 00:30:27.080 align:middle line:84%
since I wrote this book--
what part of you suffers?

00:30:27.080 --> 00:30:28.970 align:middle line:90%
What part of you suffers?

00:30:28.970 --> 00:30:31.670 align:middle line:84%
And if you start
doing that, there

00:30:31.670 --> 00:30:37.730 align:middle line:84%
was the guy, Mohana
Maharshi, Ramana Maharshi.

00:30:37.730 --> 00:30:38.530 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Oh, yes.

00:30:38.530 --> 00:30:38.730 align:middle line:90%
>>ARNTZ: Yeah.

00:30:38.730 --> 00:30:40.022 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Oh, I love him, yes.

00:30:40.022 --> 00:30:43.320 align:middle line:84%
>>ARNTZ: Yeah, and his thing
was say just, who am I?

00:30:43.320 --> 00:30:44.120 align:middle line:90%
You just meditate.

00:30:44.120 --> 00:30:45.030 align:middle line:90%
You go, who am I?

00:30:45.030 --> 00:30:45.350 align:middle line:90%
Who am I?

00:30:45.350 --> 00:30:46.730 align:middle line:90%
And that'll take you there.

00:30:46.730 --> 00:30:50.780 align:middle line:84%
Well, I started realizing if
you just say, who is suffering?

00:30:50.780 --> 00:30:52.460 align:middle line:90%
It's the same thing.

00:30:52.460 --> 00:30:54.650 align:middle line:84%
And it's a little easier
to get there because--

00:30:54.650 --> 00:30:55.775 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: --than who am I.

00:30:55.775 --> 00:30:58.040 align:middle line:84%
>>ARNTZ: Yeah, because
that's a little nebulous.

00:30:58.040 --> 00:31:01.970 align:middle line:84%
But what is it, the part
of you that is suffering?

00:31:01.970 --> 00:31:03.230 align:middle line:90%
I mean, it's kind of--

00:31:03.230 --> 00:31:06.310 align:middle line:90%
well, it's the-- uh, well, uh--

00:31:06.310 --> 00:31:10.030 align:middle line:90%


00:31:10.030 --> 00:31:11.560 align:middle line:90%
It's an interesting question.

00:31:11.560 --> 00:31:14.650 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: It has to be an
incongruency between what

00:31:14.650 --> 00:31:16.080 align:middle line:90%
the soul desires.

00:31:16.080 --> 00:31:18.580 align:middle line:84%
We're going to get into desire,
common desire in the moment.

00:31:18.580 --> 00:31:22.800 align:middle line:84%
But what the soul is desiring
to have as this experience

00:31:22.800 --> 00:31:25.780 align:middle line:84%
and growth and learning
in a lifetime as opposed

00:31:25.780 --> 00:31:29.590 align:middle line:84%
to what the lower mind or
personality or conscious mind

00:31:29.590 --> 00:31:31.540 align:middle line:90%
is up to in these parts.

00:31:31.540 --> 00:31:34.150 align:middle line:84%
And with, certainly, I
think, the vast majority

00:31:34.150 --> 00:31:37.240 align:middle line:84%
of humanity, unless
you're really

00:31:37.240 --> 00:31:40.120 align:middle line:84%
effective at deep
meditation are not

00:31:40.120 --> 00:31:42.453 align:middle line:84%
in communication
consciously with each other.

00:31:42.453 --> 00:31:44.620 align:middle line:84%
So we just kind of throw
spaghetti against the wall.

00:31:44.620 --> 00:31:47.470 align:middle line:84%
Say, hmm, bring in some
stuff from other lifetimes.

00:31:47.470 --> 00:31:48.910 align:middle line:84%
Like, hey, I'm
good at the piano.

00:31:48.910 --> 00:31:49.993 align:middle line:90%
I think I'll be a pianist.

00:31:49.993 --> 00:31:51.010 align:middle line:90%
And you don't know it.

00:31:51.010 --> 00:31:52.343 align:middle line:90%
You just want to play the piano.

00:31:52.343 --> 00:31:54.880 align:middle line:84%
But maybe that's not the
road that you're supposed

00:31:54.880 --> 00:31:56.140 align:middle line:90%
to travel in this lifetime.

00:31:56.140 --> 00:31:58.390 align:middle line:84%
You just kind of can't help
yourself 'cause it's easy.

00:31:58.390 --> 00:31:59.680 align:middle line:90%
Everybody's praising you.

00:31:59.680 --> 00:32:00.940 align:middle line:90%
So you get down that path.

00:32:00.940 --> 00:32:03.720 align:middle line:90%
And somehow, you're sinking.

00:32:03.720 --> 00:32:04.960 align:middle line:90%
It's not feeding you.

00:32:04.960 --> 00:32:06.023 align:middle line:90%
You're not growing.

00:32:06.023 --> 00:32:07.690 align:middle line:84%
So, I mean, I think
people are following

00:32:07.690 --> 00:32:11.110 align:middle line:84%
these kind of
subconscious desires

00:32:11.110 --> 00:32:12.820 align:middle line:84%
all the time without
understanding

00:32:12.820 --> 00:32:17.150 align:middle line:84%
that's not the soul's desire
for expression in that lifetime.

00:32:17.150 --> 00:32:19.030 align:middle line:84%
And that's a very
complex and deep subject.

00:32:19.030 --> 00:32:20.980 align:middle line:84%
And talk about
that a bit 'cause I

00:32:20.980 --> 00:32:22.750 align:middle line:84%
think that is where
suffering happens.

00:32:22.750 --> 00:32:26.620 align:middle line:84%
>>ARNTZ: Well, what I
came to is that suffering

00:32:26.620 --> 00:32:28.655 align:middle line:90%
is related to the soul.

00:32:28.655 --> 00:32:29.455 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Exactly.

00:32:29.455 --> 00:32:31.138 align:middle line:90%
>>ARNTZ: So it's like when you--

00:32:31.138 --> 00:32:33.430 align:middle line:84%
'cause often, you know, I
think, well, where's my soul?

00:32:33.430 --> 00:32:34.120 align:middle line:90%
I want to touch my soul.

00:32:34.120 --> 00:32:35.010 align:middle line:90%
It's like my personality.

00:32:35.010 --> 00:32:35.810 align:middle line:90%
It's my ego.

00:32:35.810 --> 00:32:37.840 align:middle line:84%
And [MUMBLES],, you go
through all that stuff.

00:32:37.840 --> 00:32:40.780 align:middle line:84%
But it's interesting when you're
suffering about something,

00:32:40.780 --> 00:32:42.170 align:middle line:90%
it really takes you internal.

00:32:42.170 --> 00:32:42.970 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Exactly.

00:32:42.970 --> 00:32:45.435 align:middle line:84%
>>ARNTZ: And that's
why, you know,

00:32:45.435 --> 00:32:46.810 align:middle line:84%
when I started
writing this book,

00:32:46.810 --> 00:32:48.920 align:middle line:84%
I kind of wrote it as a satire
of self-help books, really.

00:32:48.920 --> 00:32:50.200 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yeah, yeah, yeah.

00:32:50.200 --> 00:32:53.650 align:middle line:84%
>>ARNTZ: But once I got into
it, I realized, oh, my god, it's

00:32:53.650 --> 00:32:55.300 align:middle line:90%
the one thing we all experience.

00:32:55.300 --> 00:32:58.750 align:middle line:84%
And all this other stuff
out there, it kind of

00:32:58.750 --> 00:33:03.160 align:middle line:84%
ends up relating to, in a
very internal state, how

00:33:03.160 --> 00:33:05.170 align:middle line:90%
you're suffering.

00:33:05.170 --> 00:33:09.460 align:middle line:84%
And no one is really talking
about it as such, so.

00:33:09.460 --> 00:33:10.780 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: No.

00:33:10.780 --> 00:33:12.750 align:middle line:84%
People are not talking
about it as such,

00:33:12.750 --> 00:33:14.500 align:middle line:90%
and that's something I notice.

00:33:14.500 --> 00:33:17.800 align:middle line:84%
Even what we talked about at the
beginning of the show, people

00:33:17.800 --> 00:33:20.680 align:middle line:84%
kind of guiltily saying, I
know I shouldn't say this,

00:33:20.680 --> 00:33:23.560 align:middle line:84%
but I'm kind of
liking this, where

00:33:23.560 --> 00:33:27.220 align:middle line:84%
this quiet of the COVID
period of history, right?

00:33:27.220 --> 00:33:30.410 align:middle line:84%
It's like, I'm
just slowing down.

00:33:30.410 --> 00:33:31.210 align:middle line:90%
I'm walking.

00:33:31.210 --> 00:33:32.590 align:middle line:90%
I'm thinking.

00:33:32.590 --> 00:33:33.640 align:middle line:90%
I'm drawing again.

00:33:33.640 --> 00:33:35.830 align:middle line:90%
I'm doing the things I love.

00:33:35.830 --> 00:33:38.470 align:middle line:84%
And they're actually
living in closer harmony

00:33:38.470 --> 00:33:40.000 align:middle line:84%
because everything
ground to a stop.

00:33:40.000 --> 00:33:43.240 align:middle line:84%
Consumption ground to a stop,
except for food and such,

00:33:43.240 --> 00:33:45.400 align:middle line:90%
you know, habitual things.

00:33:45.400 --> 00:33:49.210 align:middle line:84%
That they're actually having
a moment to listen to the wh--

00:33:49.210 --> 00:33:53.205 align:middle line:84%
I call it just the whisperings
from our soul into our being,

00:33:53.205 --> 00:33:54.005 align:middle line:90%
right?

00:33:54.005 --> 00:33:56.660 align:middle line:84%
>>ARNTZ: Yep, that's
what a retreat does.

00:33:56.660 --> 00:33:59.110 align:middle line:84%
That's why you go on a
retreat is so you can--

00:33:59.110 --> 00:34:02.260 align:middle line:84%
you get rid of all
that stuff out there,

00:34:02.260 --> 00:34:04.800 align:middle line:90%
and you go internally.

00:34:04.800 --> 00:34:06.460 align:middle line:90%
And that's what we're all doing.

00:34:06.460 --> 00:34:10.600 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: So if suffering's
happening from a soul level,

00:34:10.600 --> 00:34:13.810 align:middle line:84%
OK, which it has to
be because it is deep.

00:34:13.810 --> 00:34:16.239 align:middle line:84%
Otherwise, you know, it'd
be something that can pass.

00:34:16.239 --> 00:34:18.873 align:middle line:84%
You could put some bubble gum
on it, and it would be OK.

00:34:18.873 --> 00:34:20.290 align:middle line:84%
Let's look at the
other end of it,

00:34:20.290 --> 00:34:22.449 align:middle line:84%
the repository of
everything that's been,

00:34:22.449 --> 00:34:24.909 align:middle line:84%
everything that's ever
been and ever hurt us

00:34:24.909 --> 00:34:28.310 align:middle line:84%
and made us happy in
the subconscious mind.

00:34:28.310 --> 00:34:31.150 align:middle line:84%
Because I personally
find it fascinating

00:34:31.150 --> 00:34:35.320 align:middle line:84%
how the soul, the conscious
mind, and the subconscious

00:34:35.320 --> 00:34:39.210 align:middle line:84%
work together or don't work
together in a lot of cases.

00:34:39.210 --> 00:34:42.969 align:middle line:84%
>>ARNTZ: Well, I mean,
that's part of the--

00:34:42.969 --> 00:34:45.159 align:middle line:84%
again, back to self
discovery, that's

00:34:45.159 --> 00:34:47.449 align:middle line:84%
part of the cleaning
process to align those

00:34:47.449 --> 00:34:50.230 align:middle line:84%
and once those are
better aligned.

00:34:50.230 --> 00:34:53.380 align:middle line:84%
There's one thing I want to
bring up that relates to this.

00:34:53.380 --> 00:34:55.420 align:middle line:84%
And I know that a
lot of the interviews

00:34:55.420 --> 00:34:59.140 align:middle line:84%
and stuff you talk about here
is scientifically oriented.

00:34:59.140 --> 00:35:02.710 align:middle line:84%
And people say, OK, what's
the cause of suffering?

00:35:02.710 --> 00:35:06.970 align:middle line:84%
In all this stuff I've done, the
thing that I found was the five

00:35:06.970 --> 00:35:08.550 align:middle line:84%
clichés Have you
heard about these?

00:35:08.550 --> 00:35:09.350 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: No.

00:35:09.350 --> 00:35:11.320 align:middle line:84%
>>ARNTZ: The five
clichés are from Vedanta.

00:35:11.320 --> 00:35:12.120 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: OK.

00:35:12.120 --> 00:35:14.080 align:middle line:84%
>>ARNTZ: And it
says the first one

00:35:14.080 --> 00:35:18.160 align:middle line:84%
is that all suffering is
caused by the misapprehension

00:35:18.160 --> 00:35:19.705 align:middle line:90%
of the nature of reality.

00:35:19.705 --> 00:35:20.665 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: OK.

00:35:20.665 --> 00:35:21.790 align:middle line:90%
That's very mental, though.

00:35:21.790 --> 00:35:22.370 align:middle line:90%
>>ARNTZ: I know.

00:35:22.370 --> 00:35:23.110 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: OK.

00:35:23.110 --> 00:35:24.777 align:middle line:84%
>>ARNTZ: The second
one is all suffering

00:35:24.777 --> 00:35:28.960 align:middle line:84%
is caused by attachment
to the transitory.

00:35:28.960 --> 00:35:32.230 align:middle line:90%
Next one is-- it goes on.

00:35:32.230 --> 00:35:35.047 align:middle line:84%
The last one is all
suffering is caused by the--

00:35:35.047 --> 00:35:36.755 align:middle line:84%
suffering is caused
by the fear of death.

00:35:36.755 --> 00:35:38.290 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Mm-hmm

00:35:38.290 --> 00:35:40.850 align:middle line:84%
>>ARNTZ: But all the other
ones, two through five,

00:35:40.850 --> 00:35:42.920 align:middle line:90%
are contained in the first one.

00:35:42.920 --> 00:35:43.720 align:middle line:90%
Even the--

00:35:43.720 --> 00:35:46.053 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: The misapprehension
of the nature of reality.

00:35:46.053 --> 00:35:52.030 align:middle line:84%
>>ARNTZ: So if in reality, one
never dies, you only transform,

00:35:52.030 --> 00:35:54.190 align:middle line:84%
then your fear of
death is because you're

00:35:54.190 --> 00:35:57.130 align:middle line:90%
misapprehending reality, right?

00:35:57.130 --> 00:35:59.350 align:middle line:90%
So that one thing--

00:35:59.350 --> 00:36:02.740 align:middle line:84%
and so the suffering, if you
given that, suffering, then,

00:36:02.740 --> 00:36:06.270 align:middle line:84%
is just a correction to get us
perceiving reality properly.

00:36:06.270 --> 00:36:07.270 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: I'm with you.

00:36:07.270 --> 00:36:08.562 align:middle line:90%
Yes, I hear what you're saying.

00:36:08.562 --> 00:36:13.510 align:middle line:84%
>>ARNTZ: So that's really--
it's like the part you align to.

00:36:13.510 --> 00:36:15.250 align:middle line:84%
And interestingly
enough, when you

00:36:15.250 --> 00:36:18.130 align:middle line:84%
talk to people about
near-death experiences,

00:36:18.130 --> 00:36:22.070 align:middle line:84%
where they've seen the greater
reality, when they come back,

00:36:22.070 --> 00:36:24.760 align:middle line:84%
they pretty much don't
have a fear of death.

00:36:24.760 --> 00:36:28.660 align:middle line:84%
They completely change,
and their suffering

00:36:28.660 --> 00:36:30.310 align:middle line:90%
goes, zrrr, way down.

00:36:30.310 --> 00:36:32.380 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Just
eliminating that one.

00:36:32.380 --> 00:36:34.600 align:middle line:84%
The nature of reality
is that we're, you

00:36:34.600 --> 00:36:36.480 align:middle line:90%
know, particles of light.

00:36:36.480 --> 00:36:39.570 align:middle line:90%
We're a never-ending being.

00:36:39.570 --> 00:36:42.400 align:middle line:84%
And that's something
that sounds great.

00:36:42.400 --> 00:36:45.582 align:middle line:84%
But if you haven't
experienced it, you know,

00:36:45.582 --> 00:36:47.290 align:middle line:84%
people have a hard
time handling that one

00:36:47.290 --> 00:36:49.810 align:middle line:84%
because they see someone's
dead body and all the suffering

00:36:49.810 --> 00:36:53.290 align:middle line:84%
of the process of dying and,
you know, sudden traumatic death

00:36:53.290 --> 00:36:57.070 align:middle line:84%
and so forth, which it lays
down such a traumatic imprint

00:36:57.070 --> 00:36:58.300 align:middle line:90%
in the subconscious.

00:36:58.300 --> 00:37:01.780 align:middle line:84%
To say nothing of the fact that
if one buys into the notion

00:37:01.780 --> 00:37:04.810 align:middle line:84%
that life is cyclical,
cycles of incarnations,

00:37:04.810 --> 00:37:06.610 align:middle line:84%
that we have within
our subconscious

00:37:06.610 --> 00:37:11.500 align:middle line:84%
all the myriad of ways one
can die imprinted right on us,

00:37:11.500 --> 00:37:13.780 align:middle line:84%
so we know that part of
the pain and suffering.

00:37:13.780 --> 00:37:17.100 align:middle line:84%
I think that's what holds people
down into that fear of death.

00:37:17.100 --> 00:37:18.340 align:middle line:90%
>>ARNTZ: Well, it is.

00:37:18.340 --> 00:37:21.730 align:middle line:84%
And also, I mean, just
within this one lifetime,

00:37:21.730 --> 00:37:23.230 align:middle line:84%
you're like, well,
what happens when

00:37:23.230 --> 00:37:24.525 align:middle line:90%
I don't have my hands anymore?

00:37:24.525 --> 00:37:25.325 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Exactly.

00:37:25.325 --> 00:37:27.430 align:middle line:84%
>>ARNTZ: So, you know,
it's a big thing.

00:37:27.430 --> 00:37:31.000 align:middle line:84%
But again, when the people
of the NDEs, all of that

00:37:31.000 --> 00:37:34.585 align:middle line:84%
goes away because they have a
deeper perception of reality.

00:37:34.585 --> 00:37:35.733 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yeah.

00:37:35.733 --> 00:37:37.900 align:middle line:84%
And you don't have any--
what, number two attachment

00:37:37.900 --> 00:37:38.700 align:middle line:90%
to the transitory.

00:37:38.700 --> 00:37:42.100 align:middle line:84%
>>ARNTZ: Right, 'cause you
know it's all transitory,

00:37:42.100 --> 00:37:45.430 align:middle line:84%
and you're not, that the
you, the soul, the spirit,

00:37:45.430 --> 00:37:48.573 align:middle line:84%
whatever, that's the only
thing that's not transitory.

00:37:48.573 --> 00:37:49.490 align:middle line:90%
So hang out with that.

00:37:49.490 --> 00:37:50.770 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yeah, absolutely.

00:37:50.770 --> 00:37:54.686 align:middle line:84%
So let's talk about the
virtue in suffering then.

00:37:54.686 --> 00:37:55.810 align:middle line:90%
>>ARNTZ: The virtue in it?

00:37:55.810 --> 00:37:57.620 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Some people say,
oh, there's great virtue

00:37:57.620 --> 00:37:58.440 align:middle line:90%
in suffering.

00:37:58.440 --> 00:38:00.990 align:middle line:84%
But if you look at it
from this perspective,

00:38:00.990 --> 00:38:06.500 align:middle line:84%
the virtue can be in ultimately
discovering that highest

00:38:06.500 --> 00:38:09.770 align:middle line:84%
essence of the nature of reality
and connect with the highest

00:38:09.770 --> 00:38:12.680 align:middle line:84%
essence of self, try to
live in companionship

00:38:12.680 --> 00:38:16.070 align:middle line:84%
with its desires of expression
for this incarnation.

00:38:16.070 --> 00:38:19.610 align:middle line:84%
Then any suffering can almost
be a virtue, not something

00:38:19.610 --> 00:38:21.215 align:middle line:90%
to cling to but--

00:38:21.215 --> 00:38:23.060 align:middle line:90%
>>ARNTZ: It's something that--

00:38:23.060 --> 00:38:27.950 align:middle line:84%
and again, this is coming up
with a way, a strategy or a way

00:38:27.950 --> 00:38:30.910 align:middle line:84%
that you're going to
look at what befalls you.

00:38:30.910 --> 00:38:31.710 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yes.

00:38:31.710 --> 00:38:35.780 align:middle line:84%
>>ARNTZ: So but it gets
back to that thing.

00:38:35.780 --> 00:38:38.450 align:middle line:90%
It's like a correction.

00:38:38.450 --> 00:38:39.800 align:middle line:90%
Like if you feel--

00:38:39.800 --> 00:38:43.070 align:middle line:84%
a good example is guilt. You did
something horrible to someone.

00:38:43.070 --> 00:38:45.320 align:middle line:84%
You know, and then
you're saying, OK,

00:38:45.320 --> 00:38:51.330 align:middle line:84%
I feel bad because
that was not reality.

00:38:51.330 --> 00:38:54.200 align:middle line:84%
So I'm going to go
knit it back together.

00:38:54.200 --> 00:38:55.170 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Right.

00:38:55.170 --> 00:38:57.420 align:middle line:84%
OK, now, we talk
about the big one, OK,

00:38:57.420 --> 00:38:58.880 align:middle line:90%
the Eastern traditions, right?

00:38:58.880 --> 00:38:59.680 align:middle line:90%
>>ARNTZ: Yep.

00:38:59.680 --> 00:39:02.660 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Desire is at
the root of all suffering--

00:39:02.660 --> 00:39:03.460 align:middle line:90%
that statement.

00:39:03.460 --> 00:39:04.668 align:middle line:90%
>>ARNTZ: Yeah, they say that.

00:39:04.668 --> 00:39:06.960 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: I totally disagree
with that, by the way,

00:39:06.960 --> 00:39:09.530 align:middle line:90%
completely disagree.

00:39:09.530 --> 00:39:11.930 align:middle line:84%
But it depends on the
quality of the desire.

00:39:11.930 --> 00:39:13.820 align:middle line:84%
If you're desiring
to have another drink

00:39:13.820 --> 00:39:15.620 align:middle line:84%
'cause you're also
schized out, you know,

00:39:15.620 --> 00:39:18.830 align:middle line:84%
and you're trying to cope with
life and cover your suffering,

00:39:18.830 --> 00:39:20.720 align:middle line:84%
I'm not talking about
that kind of desire.

00:39:20.720 --> 00:39:24.440 align:middle line:84%
But that subtle kind of desire
that's whispering through from

00:39:24.440 --> 00:39:28.340 align:middle line:84%
the soul and beckoning you
forward into something--

00:39:28.340 --> 00:39:33.680 align:middle line:84%
that kind of desire, I don't
think you can really live--

00:39:33.680 --> 00:39:36.770 align:middle line:84%
I don't think you can live
an effective life and a life

00:39:36.770 --> 00:39:39.770 align:middle line:84%
that's not just full of
suffering without that desire,

00:39:39.770 --> 00:39:43.050 align:middle line:84%
that thing you came to do
to express in the world.

00:39:43.050 --> 00:39:44.270 align:middle line:90%
>>ARNTZ: Yeah.

00:39:44.270 --> 00:39:46.640 align:middle line:84%
I mean, there's a lot of
ways that some of the stuff--

00:39:46.640 --> 00:39:48.837 align:middle line:84%
you know, another one's
the non-attachment.

00:39:48.837 --> 00:39:50.170 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yeah, non-attachment.

00:39:50.170 --> 00:39:52.420 align:middle line:84%
>>ARNTZ: You have people who
say, oh, non-attachment's

00:39:52.420 --> 00:39:53.220 align:middle line:90%
a thing.

00:39:53.220 --> 00:39:55.160 align:middle line:84%
And I've met people who
are so non-attached,

00:39:55.160 --> 00:39:57.630 align:middle line:84%
they don't care about
anything or anybody.

00:39:57.630 --> 00:40:00.543 align:middle line:84%
And they're kind of
miserable people, really.

00:40:00.543 --> 00:40:02.960 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Well, that can kind
of lead to narcissism, too.

00:40:02.960 --> 00:40:04.100 align:middle line:90%
>>ARNTZ: Oh, yeah.

00:40:04.100 --> 00:40:07.400 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, so all these things, you
sort of have to look at it.

00:40:07.400 --> 00:40:11.802 align:middle line:84%
The desire, I mean, if
you really have no desire,

00:40:11.802 --> 00:40:13.510 align:middle line:84%
I would have never
made "What the Bleep?"

00:40:13.510 --> 00:40:14.850 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Exactly.

00:40:14.850 --> 00:40:16.570 align:middle line:84%
That was part of
your life purpose.

00:40:16.570 --> 00:40:18.540 align:middle line:90%
Your soul was speaking to you.

00:40:18.540 --> 00:40:20.283 align:middle line:90%
And you made a beautiful film.

00:40:20.283 --> 00:40:21.700 align:middle line:84%
The people you
needed came to you.

00:40:21.700 --> 00:40:22.790 align:middle line:90%
The messages came.

00:40:22.790 --> 00:40:24.090 align:middle line:90%
>>ARNTZ: Yeah.

00:40:24.090 --> 00:40:25.780 align:middle line:90%
The ego was lucky, too.

00:40:25.780 --> 00:40:27.310 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Well,
the ego, of course.

00:40:27.310 --> 00:40:29.560 align:middle line:84%
A good ego can keep the
project moving forward.

00:40:29.560 --> 00:40:33.430 align:middle line:84%
A strong sense of self can keep
things moving forward also.

00:40:33.430 --> 00:40:34.697 align:middle line:90%
There's a place for it.

00:40:34.697 --> 00:40:36.280 align:middle line:84%
>>ARNTZ: You just
can't-- just gotta--

00:40:36.280 --> 00:40:37.080 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Will.

00:40:37.080 --> 00:40:38.957 align:middle line:84%
>>ARNTZ: You gotta
keep a little, yeah.

00:40:38.957 --> 00:40:40.790 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Yeah, you
can call it will, also.

00:40:40.790 --> 00:40:43.270 align:middle line:84%
I mean, ego's even a
misunderstood word.

00:40:43.270 --> 00:40:44.800 align:middle line:84%
But one thing I
never asked you here

00:40:44.800 --> 00:40:49.750 align:middle line:84%
is what was the
impetus speaking to you

00:40:49.750 --> 00:40:54.510 align:middle line:84%
that created the desire to
create that film to begin with?

00:40:54.510 --> 00:40:56.620 align:middle line:90%
>>ARNTZ: There was a couple.

00:40:56.620 --> 00:40:58.550 align:middle line:84%
One, and when I was
growing up, I had always

00:40:58.550 --> 00:41:00.170 align:middle line:90%
wanted to make movies.

00:41:00.170 --> 00:41:03.380 align:middle line:84%
But then I went off into
science, so that was it.

00:41:03.380 --> 00:41:08.150 align:middle line:84%
Number two, I had a
chip on my shoulder.

00:41:08.150 --> 00:41:10.430 align:middle line:84%
I had been in the spiritual
practice for 20 years

00:41:10.430 --> 00:41:12.410 align:middle line:90%
and had spiritual teachers.

00:41:12.410 --> 00:41:15.680 align:middle line:84%
And all during that
time, it was if people

00:41:15.680 --> 00:41:18.740 align:middle line:84%
knew you were meditating and
the spiritual thing, it was very

00:41:18.740 --> 00:41:20.120 align:middle line:90%
looked down upon.

00:41:20.120 --> 00:41:22.280 align:middle line:84%
Oh, Jim Jones, you going
to drink the Kool-Aid?

00:41:22.280 --> 00:41:24.173 align:middle line:90%
I mean, it was people--

00:41:24.173 --> 00:41:26.840 align:middle line:84%
and I had a chip on my shoulder,
because after 20 years of doing

00:41:26.840 --> 00:41:29.690 align:middle line:84%
this and the people I
knew that I did this with,

00:41:29.690 --> 00:41:31.900 align:middle line:84%
these were not a
bunch of flake balls.

00:41:31.900 --> 00:41:34.100 align:middle line:84%
They were people who
were reading and studying

00:41:34.100 --> 00:41:36.650 align:middle line:84%
and examining and
looking into what--

00:41:36.650 --> 00:41:37.550 align:middle line:90%
asking questions.

00:41:37.550 --> 00:41:40.520 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: I mean physicists as
a lot tend to do more of that

00:41:40.520 --> 00:41:42.075 align:middle line:90%
than other scientists as well.

00:41:42.075 --> 00:41:43.520 align:middle line:90%
>>ARNTZ: They tend to do that.

00:41:43.520 --> 00:41:45.530 align:middle line:84%
But anyone in the
spiritual field--

00:41:45.530 --> 00:41:48.680 align:middle line:84%
whether, you know, the Buddha
or whatever, they're all--

00:41:48.680 --> 00:41:51.020 align:middle line:90%
it wasn't this flaky thing.

00:41:51.020 --> 00:41:52.580 align:middle line:84%
And so I had chip
on my shoulder.

00:41:52.580 --> 00:41:55.640 align:middle line:84%
I'm like, you know, I'm tired
of being a second-class citizen.

00:41:55.640 --> 00:41:57.730 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to put this movie out,
and I'm going to use science.

00:41:57.730 --> 00:41:59.105 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: I'm
going to prove it.

00:41:59.105 --> 00:42:01.790 align:middle line:84%
>>ARNTZ: And I'm going to
show you guys that this is

00:42:01.790 --> 00:42:03.080 align:middle line:90%
a legitimate--

00:42:03.080 --> 00:42:04.340 align:middle line:90%
whether you agree or not--

00:42:04.340 --> 00:42:07.100 align:middle line:84%
this is a legitimate
area of study

00:42:07.100 --> 00:42:08.470 align:middle line:90%
as much as anything else is.

00:42:08.470 --> 00:42:10.370 align:middle line:90%
So I don't want to hear it.

00:42:10.370 --> 00:42:13.100 align:middle line:84%
So that was another
reason to do it.

00:42:13.100 --> 00:42:15.830 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Well, you may say
chip on your shoulder or ego.

00:42:15.830 --> 00:42:18.470 align:middle line:84%
But actually, it was just
a very strong expression,

00:42:18.470 --> 00:42:21.170 align:middle line:84%
in my-- this is just my
big fat opinion here--

00:42:21.170 --> 00:42:23.630 align:middle line:84%
that your soul was speaking
through to you, do this thing.

00:42:23.630 --> 00:42:27.170 align:middle line:84%
Make it so other people can
also feel safe and validated

00:42:27.170 --> 00:42:29.780 align:middle line:84%
in their own practice, and
spread the word, so to speak.

00:42:29.780 --> 00:42:32.300 align:middle line:84%
>>ARNTZ: Well, that was
the third reason, actually.

00:42:32.300 --> 00:42:35.210 align:middle line:84%
That I started-- and when
