>>ARNTZ: Sufferometer--
I brought one.

00:51:13.390 --> 00:51:14.540 align:middle line:84%
I should have brought
it to the thing.

00:51:14.540 --> 00:51:15.457 align:middle line:90%
I brought my very own.

00:51:15.457 --> 00:51:17.210 align:middle line:90%
I took it off the refrigerator.

00:51:17.210 --> 00:51:18.580 align:middle line:90%
So I wrote this chapter.

00:51:18.580 --> 00:51:21.130 align:middle line:84%
I called it the
Pseudoscience of Suffering.

00:51:21.130 --> 00:51:23.260 align:middle line:84%
And I sort of come up
with graphs and charts

00:51:23.260 --> 00:51:25.040 align:middle line:84%
and these sort of
things and cycles,

00:51:25.040 --> 00:51:27.390 align:middle line:90%
and I nerd out a bit on that.

00:51:27.390 --> 00:51:29.140 align:middle line:84%
And at the end of the
chapter, I go, well,

00:51:29.140 --> 00:51:31.600 align:middle line:84%
even a pseudoscience
needs a metric.

00:51:31.600 --> 00:51:34.420 align:middle line:90%
So my metric is a Sufferometer.

00:51:34.420 --> 00:51:38.080 align:middle line:84%
And basically, it's a little
home arts and crafts project.

00:51:38.080 --> 00:51:39.430 align:middle line:90%
You make these Sufferometers.

00:51:39.430 --> 00:51:42.740 align:middle line:84%
But essentially, there's
a dial from 0 to 100

00:51:42.740 --> 00:51:44.920 align:middle line:84%
where you say how much
are you suffering?

00:51:44.920 --> 00:51:46.520 align:middle line:90%
So I come up with this thing.

00:51:46.520 --> 00:51:48.010 align:middle line:90%
You know, it's kind of funny.

00:51:48.010 --> 00:51:49.150 align:middle line:90%
You laugh.

00:51:49.150 --> 00:51:51.260 align:middle line:90%
It keeps it light and whatnot.

00:51:51.260 --> 00:51:54.526 align:middle line:90%
And then at one point, I--

00:51:54.526 --> 00:51:57.400 align:middle line:84%
it's actually kind of funny,
talk about a small circle--

00:51:57.400 --> 00:52:02.320 align:middle line:84%
one day, I was
negotiating here with Gaia

00:52:02.320 --> 00:52:03.962 align:middle line:90%
about selling "Bleep."

00:52:03.962 --> 00:52:05.920 align:middle line:84%
And there was some of
this and there was some--

00:52:05.920 --> 00:52:07.930 align:middle line:84%
and it just didn't look
like it was going to happen,

00:52:07.930 --> 00:52:08.800 align:middle line:90%
or maybe it was.

00:52:08.800 --> 00:52:10.720 align:middle line:84%
I mean, it was just
whenever you do a deal,

00:52:10.720 --> 00:52:12.550 align:middle line:84%
that's the way it
goes, you know.

00:52:12.550 --> 00:52:15.512 align:middle line:84%
So we're going this,
and I'm like, uh,

00:52:15.512 --> 00:52:18.520 align:middle line:90%
and it was really bugging me.

00:52:18.520 --> 00:52:23.510 align:middle line:84%
And so I said, I'm just going to
go to the Sufferometer on this.

00:52:23.510 --> 00:52:25.180 align:middle line:90%
And so I'm suffering at about--

00:52:25.180 --> 00:52:28.090 align:middle line:84%
I put it up at about a
70, you know, like this.

00:52:28.090 --> 00:52:30.160 align:middle line:84%
And there's other parts
of the Sufferometer

00:52:30.160 --> 00:52:31.300 align:middle line:90%
that you sort of do.

00:52:31.300 --> 00:52:34.600 align:middle line:84%
But I did these things, and
I started looking at it.

00:52:34.600 --> 00:52:37.120 align:middle line:84%
And I started
thinking, well, I'm

00:52:37.120 --> 00:52:38.810 align:middle line:84%
suffering because
I'm in the future.

00:52:38.810 --> 00:52:40.570 align:middle line:84%
And there's a time
slider at the bottom.

00:52:40.570 --> 00:52:43.690 align:middle line:84%
You say, is your suffering in
the past, present, or future.

00:52:43.690 --> 00:52:45.310 align:middle line:84%
So my suffering
was in the future

00:52:45.310 --> 00:52:47.060 align:middle line:90%
'cause I was in the future.

00:52:47.060 --> 00:52:49.420 align:middle line:84%
So there's a wisdom
wheel where you

00:52:49.420 --> 00:52:52.600 align:middle line:84%
move it to say how you're going
to get out of the suffering.

00:52:52.600 --> 00:52:53.680 align:middle line:90%
I moved it to time.

00:52:53.680 --> 00:52:55.630 align:middle line:90%
I was going to get in the now.

00:52:55.630 --> 00:52:59.140 align:middle line:84%
So I, mm, OK, I'm going
to not think about that.

00:52:59.140 --> 00:53:01.750 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to go out
and deadhead flowers.

00:53:01.750 --> 00:53:03.400 align:middle line:84%
So I went out and
deadheaded flowers.

00:53:03.400 --> 00:53:06.350 align:middle line:84%
And after about 20
minutes, my Sufferometer,

00:53:06.350 --> 00:53:08.370 align:middle line:90%
it was down to 10.

00:53:08.370 --> 00:53:09.600 align:middle line:90%
And I'm like, oh, my god.

00:53:09.600 --> 00:53:10.630 align:middle line:90%
It actually works.

00:53:10.630 --> 00:53:14.070 align:middle line:84%
So the idea with this thing,
even though it's a crazy idea,

00:53:14.070 --> 00:53:17.040 align:middle line:84%
if every day you have to say
how much you're suffering,

00:53:17.040 --> 00:53:19.080 align:middle line:84%
you have to put a
number on it, it

00:53:19.080 --> 00:53:22.860 align:middle line:84%
does the thing of taking it out
of this gorilla in the room,

00:53:22.860 --> 00:53:24.840 align:middle line:90%
kind of hidden, not dealt with.

00:53:24.840 --> 00:53:27.360 align:middle line:84%
And you're saying this is
how much I'm suffering?

00:53:27.360 --> 00:53:31.040 align:middle line:84%
And sometimes, when I would do
it, I'd say oh, I'm about 60.

00:53:31.040 --> 00:53:32.800 align:middle line:90%
I'm, like, 60.

00:53:32.800 --> 00:53:33.630 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Really?

00:53:33.630 --> 00:53:35.880 align:middle line:84%
>>ARNTZ: You're suffering
this much on that?

00:53:35.880 --> 00:53:38.900 align:middle line:84%
And then I would just go,
like, that's ridiculous.

00:53:38.900 --> 00:53:39.940 align:middle line:90%
Bzzz.

00:53:39.940 --> 00:53:43.440 align:middle line:84%
Then I would just stop
because, again, it was a habit.

00:53:43.440 --> 00:53:45.960 align:middle line:84%
And once I realized
that-- so the crazy idea

00:53:45.960 --> 00:53:50.760 align:middle line:84%
of a Sufferometer actually
works, because, again, you're

00:53:50.760 --> 00:53:53.730 align:middle line:84%
externalizing an internal
state so you can look at it

00:53:53.730 --> 00:53:58.652 align:middle line:84%
and go, oh, with the
conscious mind, oh.

00:53:58.652 --> 00:54:00.110 align:middle line:84%
And then you get
your choice on how

00:54:00.110 --> 00:54:01.060 align:middle line:90%
you're going to deal with it.

00:54:01.060 --> 00:54:01.760 align:middle line:90%
That's the Sufferometer.

00:54:01.760 --> 00:54:02.780 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yeah, I love it.

00:54:02.780 --> 00:54:03.140 align:middle line:90%
I do.

00:54:03.140 --> 00:54:03.580 align:middle line:90%
I love it.

00:54:03.580 --> 00:54:05.600 align:middle line:84%
And you know I was
thinking, wouldn't it

00:54:05.600 --> 00:54:07.940 align:middle line:84%
be great if parents
gave each of their kids

00:54:07.940 --> 00:54:12.530 align:middle line:84%
a little Sufferometer, like,
how mad or how sad are you?

00:54:12.530 --> 00:54:14.450 align:middle line:84%
So that people
started connecting

00:54:14.450 --> 00:54:17.780 align:middle line:84%
with their authentic feelings
and the ability and freedom

00:54:17.780 --> 00:54:20.600 align:middle line:84%
to express them from
a very early age.

00:54:20.600 --> 00:54:23.630 align:middle line:84%
You know, you by
three, how sad are you?

00:54:23.630 --> 00:54:25.820 align:middle line:84%
This many or this
many, you know?

00:54:25.820 --> 00:54:27.620 align:middle line:84%
And I think it would
be a beautiful thing

00:54:27.620 --> 00:54:29.030 align:middle line:90%
to introduce into a family.

00:54:29.030 --> 00:54:31.870 align:middle line:84%
Have your family's
Sufferometer or sad chart.

00:54:31.870 --> 00:54:35.570 align:middle line:84%
>>ARNTZ: Well, what you do
you, what my wife and I do,

00:54:35.570 --> 00:54:37.310 align:middle line:84%
put them on the
refrigerator, right?

00:54:37.310 --> 00:54:39.102 align:middle line:84%
So you come down in
the morning, and if you

00:54:39.102 --> 00:54:41.240 align:middle line:84%
look at your spouses,
and it's up at around 95,

00:54:41.240 --> 00:54:43.850 align:middle line:84%
it's like, I don't think
I'm going to bring up

00:54:43.850 --> 00:54:46.320 align:middle line:90%
this new car I want to buy.

00:54:46.320 --> 00:54:48.740 align:middle line:84%
I think I'm just going to
like-- but if it's down to 3.

00:54:48.740 --> 00:54:50.823 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Especially since
she just lost her job.

00:54:50.823 --> 00:54:53.160 align:middle line:90%


00:54:53.160 --> 00:54:55.400 align:middle line:90%
>>ARNTZ: So anyway, it's--

00:54:55.400 --> 00:54:56.990 align:middle line:84%
so yeah, if you had
a family, everyone

00:54:56.990 --> 00:54:58.838 align:middle line:84%
would have their own
little Sufferometer.

00:54:58.838 --> 00:54:59.880 align:middle line:90%
You just kind of look it.

00:54:59.880 --> 00:55:02.047 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Well, it would
be a way to start becoming

00:55:02.047 --> 00:55:04.715 align:middle line:84%
emotionally honest with each
other from a very early age.

00:55:04.715 --> 00:55:06.590 align:middle line:84%
And that could actually
be a beautiful thing,

00:55:06.590 --> 00:55:08.990 align:middle line:84%
because then that garbage
doesn't have to all build up

00:55:08.990 --> 00:55:12.857 align:middle line:84%
in the subconscious to be dealt
with at a later time, you know?

00:55:12.857 --> 00:55:15.440 align:middle line:84%
>>ARNTZ: Of course, you're going
to give it to some clever kid

00:55:15.440 --> 00:55:18.643 align:middle line:84%
at age 9 who's going
to say, it's up at 95

00:55:18.643 --> 00:55:20.560 align:middle line:84%
because I have to do
this stupid Sufferometer.

00:55:20.560 --> 00:55:21.360 align:middle line:90%
That's what I'm suffering about.

00:55:21.360 --> 00:55:23.710 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Of course, too
clever for your own britches.

00:55:23.710 --> 00:55:25.817 align:middle line:90%
>>ARNTZ: Yeah, too clever.

00:55:25.817 --> 00:55:27.650 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: I wanted to
talk about your wife.

00:55:27.650 --> 00:55:28.450 align:middle line:90%
You mentioned this.

00:55:28.450 --> 00:55:31.520 align:middle line:84%
Your wife's name means
"of the sorrows."

00:55:31.520 --> 00:55:32.550 align:middle line:90%
>>ARNTZ: Deirdre.

00:55:32.550 --> 00:55:33.350 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Deirdre.

00:55:33.350 --> 00:55:34.150 align:middle line:90%
>>ARNTZ: Deirdre.

00:55:34.150 --> 00:55:35.750 align:middle line:90%
Deidre of the Sorrows.

00:55:35.750 --> 00:55:38.580 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: So she has a name
that is kind of weighted with

00:55:38.580 --> 00:55:39.380 align:middle line:90%
suffering.

00:55:39.380 --> 00:55:42.530 align:middle line:90%
>>ARNTZ: Well, her--

00:55:42.530 --> 00:55:46.430 align:middle line:84%
I got to tell you, the
book really came about--

00:55:46.430 --> 00:55:49.760 align:middle line:84%
one day, I was walking
through the living room,

00:55:49.760 --> 00:55:51.070 align:middle line:90%
and she's laying on the couch.

00:55:51.070 --> 00:55:53.720 align:middle line:84%
Her back is out and
in little lot of pain.

00:55:53.720 --> 00:55:55.838 align:middle line:84%
I said, honey, what
do you want to do?

00:55:55.838 --> 00:55:57.005 align:middle line:90%
And she didn't say anything.

00:55:57.005 --> 00:55:57.805 align:middle line:90%
What are you doing?

00:55:57.805 --> 00:56:01.700 align:middle line:84%
She goes, I just want
to lay here and suffer.

00:56:01.700 --> 00:56:02.570 align:middle line:90%
And I just stop.

00:56:02.570 --> 00:56:04.090 align:middle line:90%
I'm like what?

00:56:04.090 --> 00:56:05.030 align:middle line:90%
No one says, I said--

00:56:05.030 --> 00:56:05.210 align:middle line:90%
[INTERPOSING VOICES]

00:56:05.210 --> 00:56:07.000 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Not
your go-to emotion.

00:56:07.000 --> 00:56:10.520 align:middle line:84%
>>ARNTZ: She goes, yes, I'm
perfecting my suffering.

00:56:10.520 --> 00:56:13.130 align:middle line:84%
And I started to laugh,
just the way she said it.

00:56:13.130 --> 00:56:14.630 align:middle line:84%
And then I said
the infamous line,

00:56:14.630 --> 00:56:16.310 align:middle line:84%
someone should write
a self-help book,

00:56:16.310 --> 00:56:19.670 align:middle line:84%
"How to Suffer in 10 Easy
Steps," and then off we go.

00:56:19.670 --> 00:56:24.320 align:middle line:84%
So apparently with her family
that that was something her--

00:56:24.320 --> 00:56:25.970 align:middle line:90%
you say, where's mom?

00:56:25.970 --> 00:56:28.940 align:middle line:84%
And her dad would say, oh,
she's upstairs suffering.

00:56:28.940 --> 00:56:31.130 align:middle line:90%
She does it so well.

00:56:31.130 --> 00:56:33.800 align:middle line:84%
So her dad gave her
the name Deirdre,

00:56:33.800 --> 00:56:38.210 align:middle line:84%
which in Irish folklore, it
was Deirdre of the Sorrows

00:56:38.210 --> 00:56:41.300 align:middle line:84%
because there's this whole thing
about that she goes through.

00:56:41.300 --> 00:56:43.480 align:middle line:90%
So that was kind of the--

00:56:43.480 --> 00:56:45.980 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Yeah, and there's
another point in the book where

00:56:45.980 --> 00:56:47.990 align:middle line:84%
you say she brought
something through.

00:56:47.990 --> 00:56:49.190 align:middle line:90%
She's quite intuitive.

00:56:49.190 --> 00:56:53.390 align:middle line:84%
When you were in Siena
at the Basilica, right?

00:56:53.390 --> 00:56:57.860 align:middle line:84%
Oh, god, I love Siena, and
I love the Duomo in Siena.

00:56:57.860 --> 00:56:59.530 align:middle line:84%
We just went there
exactly a year ago.

00:56:59.530 --> 00:57:00.530 align:middle line:90%
It's so beautiful.

00:57:00.530 --> 00:57:02.810 align:middle line:84%
And she brought
something through talking

00:57:02.810 --> 00:57:04.160 align:middle line:90%
with St. Catherine, right?

00:57:04.160 --> 00:57:05.420 align:middle line:90%
And I wrote it down here.

00:57:05.420 --> 00:57:08.750 align:middle line:84%
"Catherine wants you to know
suffering was a pathway to God,

00:57:08.750 --> 00:57:11.400 align:middle line:90%
but this is no longer the way.

00:57:11.400 --> 00:57:14.220 align:middle line:84%
It is not the end of
suffering, however."

00:57:14.220 --> 00:57:16.276 align:middle line:90%
What did that mean?

00:57:16.276 --> 00:57:19.110 align:middle line:84%
>>ARNTZ: It means that
the idea that you would--

00:57:19.110 --> 00:57:21.510 align:middle line:84%
back then when
Catherine did this,

00:57:21.510 --> 00:57:23.285 align:middle line:84%
you would consciously
take on suffering.

00:57:23.285 --> 00:57:24.660 align:middle line:84%
You know, there
were other people

00:57:24.660 --> 00:57:27.077 align:middle line:84%
like if you did something bad,
you'd put on the hair shirt

00:57:27.077 --> 00:57:28.000 align:middle line:90%
and whip yourself.

00:57:28.000 --> 00:57:28.720 align:middle line:90%
So you would suffer--

00:57:28.720 --> 00:57:29.887 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Self-flagellation

00:57:29.887 --> 00:57:31.440 align:middle line:90%
>>ARNTZ: --and all that stuff.

00:57:31.440 --> 00:57:36.660 align:middle line:84%
That was looked as a pathway
in order to holiness.

00:57:36.660 --> 00:57:40.810 align:middle line:84%
But that's like, OK, that
was a phase we went through,

00:57:40.810 --> 00:57:43.170 align:middle line:84%
but it's time to
move beyond that.

00:57:43.170 --> 00:57:45.900 align:middle line:84%
It's time to move
beyond that and to have

00:57:45.900 --> 00:57:48.780 align:middle line:84%
a different relationship
with suffering.

00:57:48.780 --> 00:57:50.240 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: A more conscious one.

00:57:50.240 --> 00:57:51.490 align:middle line:90%
>>ARNTZ: A more conscious one.

00:57:51.490 --> 00:57:55.020 align:middle line:84%
And it was-- we were
in the cathedral there.

00:57:55.020 --> 00:57:59.050 align:middle line:84%
And that's where, you know,
her skull is in that cathedral

00:57:59.050 --> 00:57:59.850 align:middle line:90%
there.

00:57:59.850 --> 00:58:03.180 align:middle line:84%
And she's telling me this stuff,
and we had our tour guide.

00:58:03.180 --> 00:58:05.400 align:middle line:84%
And the tour guide's
eyes were like saucers,

00:58:05.400 --> 00:58:08.430 align:middle line:84%
and all her hair is
standing up on end saying,

00:58:08.430 --> 00:58:11.000 align:middle line:90%
what is going on?

00:58:11.000 --> 00:58:12.670 align:middle line:10%
Well, this is what Deirdre does.

00:58:12.670 --> 00:58:15.570 align:middle line:10%
She's talking to Catherine,
believe it or not.

00:58:15.570 --> 00:58:18.045 align:middle line:90%
And it was electric.

00:58:18.045 --> 00:58:20.550 align:middle line:90%


00:58:20.550 --> 00:58:23.490 align:middle line:10%
And that was actually before
I was writing the book.

00:58:23.490 --> 00:58:25.410 align:middle line:90%
And so it just came back to me.

00:58:25.410 --> 00:58:27.720 align:middle line:84%
I'm like, oh, my
god, that's something

00:58:27.720 --> 00:58:31.230 align:middle line:84%
that we're going to redefine--
how we look at suffering.

00:58:31.230 --> 00:58:34.920 align:middle line:84%
Because back then, it was
just, again, hurt myself.

00:58:34.920 --> 00:58:38.460 align:middle line:84%
And part of that was because
of the whole church's focus

00:58:38.460 --> 00:58:40.450 align:middle line:84%
on Jesus and suffering
on the cross.

00:58:40.450 --> 00:58:41.250 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Right.

00:58:41.250 --> 00:58:44.410 align:middle line:84%
>>ARNTZ: That suffering
became really a part of it.

00:58:44.410 --> 00:58:46.995 align:middle line:84%
And it's like, it's time
to move beyond that.

00:58:46.995 --> 00:58:48.870 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: To do it consciously.

00:58:48.870 --> 00:58:51.360 align:middle line:84%
So just as you
brought it forward,

00:58:51.360 --> 00:58:54.090 align:middle line:84%
everything you did in "What
the Bleep Do We Know?"

00:58:54.090 --> 00:58:57.505 align:middle line:84%
in terms of understanding
this whole matrix of belief

00:58:57.505 --> 00:58:59.880 align:middle line:84%
and the effect on our lives
and what we can bring through

00:58:59.880 --> 00:59:00.750 align:middle line:90%
in ourselves.

00:59:00.750 --> 00:59:02.730 align:middle line:84%
Now, you're bringing
to us the notion

00:59:02.730 --> 00:59:05.010 align:middle line:84%
that we need to address the
suffering underneath all

00:59:05.010 --> 00:59:08.370 align:middle line:84%
of these desires and so
forth so that we can do

00:59:08.370 --> 00:59:09.960 align:middle line:90%
that in a more conscious way.

00:59:09.960 --> 00:59:11.250 align:middle line:90%
So you're still at it.

00:59:11.250 --> 00:59:12.430 align:middle line:90%
>>ARNTZ: I am still at it.

00:59:12.430 --> 00:59:14.280 align:middle line:10%
And I got to tell
you, I am still

00:59:14.280 --> 00:59:18.120 align:middle line:10%
so surprised I wrote a book on
suffering because it's not my--

00:59:18.120 --> 00:59:19.620 align:middle line:10%
I mean, you know,
I'm kind of nerdy.

00:59:19.620 --> 00:59:20.537 align:middle line:10%
>> REGINA: Yeah, yeah.

00:59:20.537 --> 00:59:23.010 align:middle line:10%
>>ARNTZ: You know, da-da-da-da
da-da-da and to do that.

00:59:23.010 --> 00:59:25.170 align:middle line:10%
But I got tricked into it.

00:59:25.170 --> 00:59:26.820 align:middle line:10%
I mean, the only way
